title: pink party rhubarb pie
directions: Bake the pie shells in two pie plates.
Dice 2 cups rhubarb. Put into a saucepan with the sugar and cook until soft.
Stir in the jello until it is dissolved.
Let stand until cool.
Prepare the whipping cream or Dream Whip or use the Cool Whip and fold in the lemon juice.
Fold this into the cooled rhubarb mixture and then pour equal amounts into the pie shells.
Refrigerate for about 3 hours.
Great spring dessert.

title: beets ala orange
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid in saucepan. Add orange juice and cornstarch, stirring until cornstarch is completely dissolved. Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear. Add beets, butter, sugar and orange peel.
Heat through. Do not boil.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Makes 3 pies.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls to cover cookie or pizza pan.
Bake until done.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Sprinkle on cheese, peppers and broccoli.

title: super spaghetti
directions: Lightly brown beef.
Add onion, oregano and garlic.
Cook until onion is tender.
Blend in soup, water and vinegar.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: firehouse barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and heat in saucepan; cool and store in refrigerator to be used as needed.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles course meal.
Add milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Set aside.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients in a blender or mixer.
Pour into freezer and finish filling to the fill line on can with milk.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: rum cream pie
directions: Shave chocolate into curls with a sharp knife and set aside. Combine water, gelatin and sugar in saucepan over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Slowly dribble mixture into beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Return mixture to saucepan; cook until slightly thickened.
Cool slightly; add rum.
Chill until partially set.

title: old fashion oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together.
Add flour, crisco and vanilla, mixing well.
Add oatmeal, pecans and coconut.
Spoon out onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for approx. 15 minutes.

title: cooking a cheese pumpkin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut crosswise.
Remove strings and seeds.
Place shell up on the oven racks for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Carefully, with oven mitts, turn over.
Cook another 20 to 30 minutes until fork will go easily through flesh.
Remove from oven; cool.
Scrape flesh into large bowl.
Can be stored in refrigerator up to a week; in freezer up to 6 months.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In bowl, beat eggs until stiff.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Turn into greased casserole dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until center is firm.

title: people chow
directions: Melt together the peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour chocolate mix over cereal, raisins and peanuts.
Mix until all is coated.
Place mixture in bag with powdered sugar and shake until evenly coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: didy's vegetable soup
directions: Cook soup bone on medium heat.
Add seasonings to taste.
Add tomato juice, onions and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add rest of vegetables and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: casserole
directions: Put potatoes, onions, cheese and patties (cut into small pieces) into layers.
Add water.
At 350°, cook about 1 hour or until done.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients and pour 1/2 into greased and floured Bundt cake pan. Sprinkle brown sugar mixture over top.
Pour rest of cake mixture over this.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: springtime quiche
directions: Toss cheese, spinach and flour together.
Spread in pie shell. Mix milk and eggs, salt and nutmeg.
Pour over spinach.
Fluff to mix.
Break cooked bacon on top.
Sprinkle a little more nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until egg is cooked.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Cut chicken in cubes. Put in large skillet with butter. Cook until chicken turns white. Add pepper and garlic. Heat 3 to 4 minutes until all is hot. Add salsa; remove from fire. Tear tortillas into pieces. Layer in 9 x 13 baking dish with chicken mixture and cheese. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour in greased casserole dish. Bake at 300 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy apple butter
directions: May add 1 box Sure-Jell, if desired.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolk, 1 tablespoon heavy cream, pineapple, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Add beaten egg white; set aside.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and quarter artichoke hearts.
Mix with remaining ingredients in a small casserole.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: avocado-fruit salad with honey-yogurt dressing
directions: Arrange lettuce, avocado, grapefruit, walnuts and grapes on salad plates; serve immediately with dressing.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and white sugar in plastic bag.
Cut biscuits into fourths and shake in sugar mixture to coat biscuits.
Put into a greased pan.
Melt margarine and brown sugar on low heat. Pour over biscuits and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and dump out onto a cake plate and serve.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil noodles in water until done; drain and put back in pot. Mix egg and milk together and add to noodles.
Crush tomatoes with hand and add to noodles, along with some juice.
Cut 1 lb. cheese into chunks and add to noodles.
Add salt and pepper and stir together.
Put in 9 x 15 inch pan.
Grate remaining 1/2 lb. cheese and sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cream of zucchini soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Add zucchini; cook until tender.
Put in blender to make smooth mixture.
Return to pot; heat and melt in cheese (do not boil).
Simmer.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; cool and peel.
Slice and place in casserole dish.
Melt oleo.
Saute onion and mushrooms.
Add Ro-Tel and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Salt and pepper potatoes.
Pour cheese mixture over potatoes.
Serve.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix together cream cheese (room temperature), green chiles and onion.
Spread a layer of cream cheese mixture on tortilla.
Roll tortilla and place in refrigerator for at least 1 or 2 hours.
Cut each tortilla into 1 to 2-inch slices and serve with picante sauce.

title: egg custards
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and flour well, then add milk, butter and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour 15 minutes at 225°.

title: white cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat egg whites.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and buttermilk to sugar mixture.
Mix well and add flavoring.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until done.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with ice.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over the oats.
Set aside. Cream together the oleo, brown sugar and white sugar. Add the eggs.
Mix together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Pour oatmeal over creamed mixture and blend.
Add the flour mix and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix all together just to blend; don't overbeat (I did that at first).
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Delicious served with whipped cream.

title: orange-coconut balls
directions: Mix
vanilla wafer crumbs, 1/4 cup melted butter, 1 cup confectioners
sugar,
nuts
and
cup frozen orange juice together.	Make
into
balls.
Combine
tablespoons
soft butter,
2 cups confectioners sugar and orange juice together. Dip balls into mixture, then roll in coconut.

title: mama's best meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: fruited cheese mold
directions: Drain raspberries; reserve liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to make 1 cup.
Pour liquid in 1-quart saucepan.
Add sugar.
Sprinkle gelatin over liquid.
Let stand 5 minutes on low heat until gelatin is dissolved, stirring constantly.

title: sally eggleston's hot party sandwiches
directions: Brown meat;
drain
off fat.
Add cheese chunks and mix until melted.
Add seasonings and mix.
Spread small amount of meat mixture
on
bread slices.
You can freeze until ready to serve or broil
for
several minutes until bubbly hot.
Serve hot.
If they
have been frozen, just remove from freezer and broil to serve.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over vegetables.
The longer it sets, the better it is.

title: macaroni and chicken casserole
directions: Mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove 1 hour before baking.
Stir well.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Use pastry for single crust pie.
Combine first 4 ingredients. Cook and stir the mixture until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Separate 4 eggs.
Set whites aside.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Gradually stir 1 cup of hot mixture into yolks.
Return mixture to saucepan. Bring to boil; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat. Add coconut, butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Bring water, broccoli and bouillon to boil.
Simmer until tender.
Do not drain.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook over medium heat until thick and creamy.
Add to broccoli and liquid. Stir well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen pink lemonade sundae pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in bottled lemon juice and food coloring.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Freeze or chill 6 hours or until firm.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish as desired.
Freeze leftovers.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend. Pour into pie shell, sprinkle with nutmeg and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken poppy seed casserole
directions: Place chicken into greased baking dish.
Pour mixture of sour cream and soup over chicken.
Sprinkle poppy seeds over mixture, then top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Place small pats of margarine on crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Mix soups and sour cream. Pour over chicken. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake 30 more minutes at 350°. Serve with noodles or rice.

title: ham barbecues
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in margarine.
In large pot, mix first 3 ingredients with next 8.
Simmer for 30 to 60 minutes. Serve on hamburg buns.

title: easter egg candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Roll into balls and shape into eggs.
If coconut is dry, add enough milk for consistency to roll easily.
Let stand approximately 1 hour.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Do not let water boil, only until melted.
Dip eggs in chocolate and place on waxed paper and refrigerate until chocolate has set.
Yields approximately 2 1/2 pounds.

title: turtle caramel cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour half the batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
While cooling, mix and heat milk, margarine and caramels until melted.
Pour over cooled cake when melted.
Over the caramel mixture, spread the chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining cake batter over top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate lush dessert
directions: Mash in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: 3 bean
directions: Boil sausage for 8 minutes; remove and slice.
Brown in frying pan.
Combine all ingredients; cook in crock-pot or oven for 2 to 3 hours at slow heat (300°).
Makes a large amount.
If in a hurry, you can cook at 375° for 1 hour.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Dredge fruit and nuts with flour.
Sift together flour and baking powder; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar together; set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Add dry mixture, creamed mixture, egg whites and milk together, mixing thoroughly; add lemon extract.
Fold in fruit and mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, then reduce oven to 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
This can be baked in a loaf pan or 2 small pans.

title: lemon bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt on waxed paper.
Cream sugar and butter.
Beat egg whites and lemon rind.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well until blended.
Stir in milk. Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan 40 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven. Transfer to wire rack.
Cool completely before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients and put in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fluffy white cake frosting
directions: Mix this together and put in top of double boiler with boiling water, beating with electric mixer for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: barbecue corn
directions: Salt and pepper corn in shucks to taste.
Soak in salty ice water until shucks are wet.
Lay on grill.
Poke corn with ice pick.
When done, remove shucks and season to taste.

title: thick chili
directions: Crumble ground beef into Dutch oven.
Add onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Cook until beef is brown and vegetables are tender; stir frequently.
Add remaining ingredients except kidney beans. Cook over medium heat for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add kidney beans and simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.

title: sheath cake
directions: Place sugar and flour in a bowl.
Mix well.
In saucepan, bring shortening, oleo, cocoa and water to a rapid boil.
Remove from heat and pour over sugar and flour, mixing well. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
About 5 minutes before cake is done, prepare the frosting and ice cake while it is hot.

title: apple jelly
directions: Combine apple juice and pectin in a large Dutch oven or double boiler. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Add sugar and bring mixture to a full, rolling boil. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove mixture from heat. Skim off foam with metal spoon. Pour jelly in jar.

title: jamaican curried chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken. Rub with lime juice and cut into small pieces.
Lightly brown them, a few at a time, in oil.
Set the browned chicken aside in a bowl.
In the oil in which the chicken was browned, saute the onions and garlic, then add the curry powder; stir. Add the tomatoes, hot pepper slices, whole pepper, black pepper and a little salt.
Pour in water and stir. Add the chicken pieces.
Bring to
a boil, then lower the heat. Cover cooking pot and simmer until chicken is tender.
Taste for salt just before liquid is reduced to a gravy, about 1 hour.

title: snicker doodle cookies
directions: Mix ingredients into a bowl to form dough.
Roll into balls about the size of a small walnut.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Do not flatten.
Bake at 300° for 10-12 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add onion, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning and tomato paste.
Blend well.
Unroll and separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 9-inch pie pan, pressing pieces together to form crust.
Turn meat mixture into unbaked crust and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese and chili dip
directions: Combine cheeses, lemon juice, hot sauce and bouillon in mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until smooth. Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Chill.
Yields 2 cups.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add eggs and other ingredients.
Add berries last.
Bake in 2 square or 3 round layers at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: yeast dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Add oil and yeast water to flour.
Stir dough until well mixed.
Place dough in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise until double in bulk.

title: italian beef
directions: Stuff roast in good size crock or slow cooker.
Dump all ingredients minus cheese over roast.
Slow cook 8 to 10 hours. Buy some of your favorite hoagies or Italian bread (long loaf). Using tongs, fill buns with mixture; top with grated Mozzarella to taste.
Broil until cheese is melted.
Serve at football parties. Spicy.
Chicago style sandwich.

title: russian tea
directions: Extract juice from lemons and oranges. Boil the rinds in 1 quart of water with cloves for 5 minutes. Strain and add sugar. Mix juices and water to tea. Serve very hot.

title: mushrooms in oil-garlic sauce(microwave)
directions: Place oil and garlic in a 2-quart microwave bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High 2 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms. Re-cover and cook on High 5 minutes.
Stir twice, remove and serve with minced parsley, sprinkled on top.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar (1/2 cup at a time); add eggs 1 at a time.
Add flour, buttermilk and pecans.
Fill unbaked pie shell. Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in top of a double boiler. Add margarine, beaten egg yolks and milk.
Cook over boiling water, under medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Pour into cooled baked pie shell and top with meringue and spread until sides are sealed.
Brown meringue in a 350° oven, about 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage and add remaining ingredients.
Spoon into mini baking tins.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: 5 nut brownies(fudge type)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in chocolate.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy marshmallow four layer bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix cake mix, butter and water until blended.
Pat into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 22 minutes.
Layer marshmallows, candy and peanuts over crust.
Bake for 2 to 3 minutes, or until marshmallows begin to melt.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 24.

title: ooey gooey bars
directions: Press one package frozen cookie dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan, filling the whole pan.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and eggs well; pour mixture on top of cookie dough.
Pinch off globs of second dough package and drop on top of the cheese mixture, sporadically. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and drain.
Roll out bread dough. Put sausage down center of bread; sprinkle on cheese.
Roll into a long loaf.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Beat 1 egg in a bowl. Paint loaf with beaten egg.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll in balls; dip in sugar.
Flatten with fork.
Chill.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: simple turtle soup
directions: Put all ingredients in pot.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake cookies at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and turn in powdered sugar.

title: hamburger pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (for metal pie plate, 425°).
Sift flour before measuring; cut Crisco into flour with pastry blender or two knives until mixture is uniform.
Mix onion salt and water; sprinkle on water a tablespoon at a time; toss lightly with a fork.
Work dough into a firm ball with your hands.
Divide dough in half and form two flat circles.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out bottom crust until 1 1/2 inches larger than inverted 9-inch pie plate.
Fold circle in half; lift dough into pie plate. Trim even with edge.
Roll out top crust the same way.
Add pie filling (recipe follows)
and cover with top crust; trim 1/2-inch beyond edge.
Fold top crust edge under edge of bottom crust; seal and flute with fingers or fork.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring the sugar, water and Karo syrup to a boil.
Add peanuts and food coloring.
Cook until it reaches hard boil stage.
Remove from heat and add margarine and salt.
Beat until thick.
Pour onto buttered pan.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Spread bean dip in oblong dish.
Then go to the next ingredient as listed.
Spread each over the other. Top with black olives.
Use as much or as little to suit your taste.

title: rice salad
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, salt and pepper. Add rice, tomatoes, cucumber and onion; toss.
Serve chilled.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Bon appetit!

title: brie popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450.
Generously grease 24 small muffin cups, 1 3/4 x 1-inch.
Beat eggs slightly in medium bowl with fork or wire whisk.
Beat in flour, milk, sugar and salt just until smooth (do not overbeat).
Fill cups about 2/3 full.
Bake 5 minutes.

title: two toned salad
directions: Mix lime jello with boiling hot water.	Add pear juice, salt and
vinegar.
Put	the
mixture in bottom of each mold, saving half in the refrigerator until set enough to whip with ginger
and cream cheese.
Fold in pears and pour into molds. Refrigerate.

title: macaroni tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain and cool.
Add onion, carrot, celery, green pepper, salt, pepper and celery seed. Mix together.
Set aside.
In large measuring cup, add mayonnaise and vinegar.
Mix together until smooth.
Add milk (or water), mixing until smooth and of pouring consistency.
Pour onto macaroni and mix all together.
Mix in peas and tuna.
Place in serving bowl.
May garnish with sliced tomatoes and parsley.
Chill.
(If salad is not moist enough, mix together more of mayo mixture and add to salad.)

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix dry pudding mix with the Cool Whip until well blended.
Add the pineapple, nuts and marshmallows.

title: grilled catfish
directions: Skin and fillet catfish.
Combine all ingredients except catfish in bowl, mixing well.
Pour marinade over catfish in shallow dish.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Cook 4 inches above hot coals on greased grill for 5 minutes on each side, or until fish tests done, basting frequently with reserved marinade.

title: reuben pie
directions: Cook beef. Add all ingredients except grated Swiss cheese. Place half of the meat mixture in deep dish pie shell. Top with half the grated cheese. Add the other half of the meat mixture and top with remaining grated cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: hot cheddar stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse, pat dry and remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems (about 1 1/2 cups); set aside.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together. Cook in microwave for 14 minutes. Beat egg whites stiff and add vanilla.
Have this ready and pour over sugar mixture. Beat until ready.

title: almost heaven cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed; bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
When done, prick cake generously with fork.
Pour pineapple over top while cake is hot.
Blend pudding with milk and beat in cream cheese.
Spread over pineapple and cover with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.
If desired, garnish with chopped nuts and/or coconut.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: In a heavy saucepan, bring the cream just to a boil.
Remove from heat and immediately add the chocolate pieces and butter. Stir until all the chocolate pieces and butter are melted.
Beat with a spoon until well mixed.
Pour into a bowl and cover (let the chocolate mixture cool to room temperature before covering). Chill in the refrigerator overnight.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on a plate.
Re-chill in refrigerator.
Dip each ball into melted chocolate to cover.
Set on waxed paper to harden.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegies, soup, 1/2 cup of cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 cup of onions.
Pour in 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: white bread
directions: Mix warm water, yeast, honey, salt, oil, eggs and 5 cups of water.
Beat this with electric mixer.
Add last 5 cups flour by hand.
Let raise in bowl.
Put in 4 loaf pans and let raise again. (Dough will be sticky).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: libby's lemon bars
directions: Combine margarine, 2 cups of the flour and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and blend until smooth.
Pat the dough into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Combine eggs, sugar and lemon juice and mix well.
Pour over pastry.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with additional confectioners sugar and cut into small bars.

title: mustard chow chow
directions: Cook each vegetable separate until done.
Mix mustard, sugar, vinegar and turmeric.
Put vegetables in juice and bring to a boil and boil 15 minutes.
Jar and seal.

title: czech country soup
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add uncooked noodles, water, bouillon cubes, carrots, potatoes and mushroom soup.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: yogurt fruit salad
directions: First, you have adult help you cut up the fruit.
Next, put them into the bowl.
Then put in the yogurt in bowl and stir. Ready to serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well with rotary beater eggs, sugar, Karo and butter. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with pecans.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.
May serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Beat egg whites on medium speed until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff enough to stand in moist peaks, about 1 minute.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add vanilla.
Continue beating until meringue is stiff and sugar well blended.
Add cornstarch
(this keeps meringue from "weeping").
Mix well.
Pile meringue on top of filling.
Spread, bringing well onto crust. Swirl with spatula to make meringue stand in points.
Bake at 325° about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Don't get it too brown.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix and dry pudding in a bowl.
Mix eggs, oil and cool 7-Up in mixer bowl; beat well, gradually adding dry mixture. Grease and flour a tube pan for cake.
Put mixture in tube pan and bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Top with powdered sugar.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil spaghetti.
Brown ground beef; add onion, garlic and oregano.
Mix spaghetti sauce with ground beef.

In 9 x 13 in. dish, layer 1/2 of spaghetti, 1/2 meat sauce and cheddar cheese. Layer rest of spaghetti, rest of meat sauce and mozzarella cheese. Mix 1/2 can water with mushroom soup and pour over casserole. Bake for 30 min. at 350 degrees.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: dotty's strawberry sour cream jello
directions: Mix Jell-O, boiling water, frozen strawberries, mashed bananas and nuts together.
Pour half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan. Let that gel.
Spread with sour cream.
Pour other half on top. Chill.

title: "patty's" banana bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Cut in shortening like for pie crust.
Mix together using a fork.
Add eggs and bananas. Blend until mixed (note:
do not use mixer; don't overmix). Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, approximately.
(Can use muffin tins, etc.; adjust baking time.)

title: buffalo chip cookies ("best cookies ever!")
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugars. Add eggs, vanilla, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix well.
Next, mix in flour and oatmeal.
Stir in cornflakes, then any remaining ingredients.
Bake for 11 to 13 minutes.

title: wash day casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 9-inch cast-iron skillet, slowly melt butter, turning pan to coat sides and bottom.
Mix eggs with fork until light and creamy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix just until blended. Pour into prepared skillet or casserole, if preferred.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer (or until set).
Can be served hot or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple surprise pie
directions: Mix together the pineapple and vanilla pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in graham cracker crust. Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate several hours.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time. Beat well. Add flour, baking powder and milk; add flavorings. Pour into tube pan that has been greased and lightly floured; bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until chilled.

title: spinach casserole #1
directions: In a small frying pan melt butter; saute onion and cooked and very well drained spinach to onions.
Cut cream cheese up and add to spinach.
Stir until cheese melts slightly.
Mix egg and add to spinach.
Add bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Add chicken bouillon (powder is better) or cut up a cube.
Mix well.
Put mixture in a greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
You may sprinkle more Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs on top before baking, if you wish.

title: cherry nut pie
directions: Mix well.
Spoon into crusts and chill.

title: my favorite quiche
directions: Combine and blend mayonnaise, milk and well beaten eggs.
Add chopped chilies and olives.
Stir in cornstarch, pepper, garlic powder and grated cheese (save a little for later).
Pour all ingredients into unbaked, thin pie shell.
Put a little cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Put oven down to 350° and bake for 25 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Cut and serve with a green salad and fruit.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Chop finely the onion, pepper and cheese.
Blend in all other ingredients except the rice.
Mix last with rice and pour into casserole. Cover and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 or 7.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Roll out defrosted shells until thin.
Spread with Dijon mustard.
Top with chicken slices.
Roll up and tuck sides under. Spray cookie sheet.
Put chicken bundles on sheet.
Apply prepared dressing mix on top of bundles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into 2-inch pieces.
Saute eggplant in half of the butter until opaque.
Remove to greased casserole dish. Saute onion and green pepper in remaining butter.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add to eggplant.
Add tomatoes to casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until tomatoes are bubbly and cheese has melted.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Mix well, but don't beat too long.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Cool and top with frosting.

title: marguerita bars
directions: Butter eighteen 2-inch cupcake tins.
Bake at 350°.
Mix thoroughly first 5 ingredients.
Fill the tins 2/3 full.
Put a pecan on each one.
Bake until the cakes shrink slightly from the pans, 8 to 15 minutes.
Makes 18.

title: green bean treat
directions: Cook bacon and crumble.
Use 1 tablespoon bacon drippings to saute onion.
Blend in cornstarch, salt and mustard.
Drain beans. Reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir liquid into skillet.
Cook stirring constantly until thick and bubbly.
Stir in sugar and vinegar. Add beans; heat until bubbly hot.
Sprinkle with bacon and egg.

title: avis' chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Cook onion and celery ribs until tender. Combine with tomatoes, tomato paste, chili seasoning, chili (no beans), kidney beans, sugar, salt, pepper and chili powder to taste.
Simmer until you can't stand it any more.
Enjoy.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring water to boil, drop in crackers.
Place in an uncooked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put dabs of butter on top. Bake at 350` for 30 minutes.
Tastes like real apple pie.

title: sunshine vanilla cookies cheese tarts
directions: Mix
first
four
ingredients
and beat until light and fluffy.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each 2-inch (midget) paper
cup.
Fill about 3/4 full.
Bake 12 minutes.
Cool then top with
cherry
pie filling (use 2-inch midget cupcake muffin). Makes 40.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese with an electric mixer until creamy.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat until smooth.
Pour into pastry shell.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Put butter, sugar and cinnamon in saucepan and cook until melted.
Cut apples into 8 pieces each.
Wrap each apple piece in a crescent roll and place in a 9 X 13 baking dish with folded side down.
Pour butter mixture over rolls.
Pour Mountain Dew over all.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: baked squash
directions: Precook squash by steaming until just tender.
Mix eggs into mashed squash.
Add onion, mashed saltines, salt and pepper to taste, sugar and melted butter.
Mix together well.
Pour into glass baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in a large skillet. Stir in barbecue sauce and water. Cover and cook over medium-low heat 20 minutes or until tender.
Stir in rice and corn.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix ingredients well and stor in a tightly covered jar.
Add 2 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water for tea, hot or cold.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower by package directions; drain.
Combine all ingredients except chives.
Blend until smooth with electric blender and blend until smooth.
Add chives; heat well and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hamburger potato hot dish
directions: Brown meat and onion until almost done; add celery.
Put in layers in baking dish; then heat soup together.
Rinse cans with little water or milk and pour over hot dish.
Bake until potatoes are done, about 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Put in a pie pan and press out.

title: mom's pickled eggs
directions: Pack shelled eggs in a large jar.
Add all remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over eggs. Let pickle for about 10 days to 2 weeks.

title: lo-cal cranberry sauce
directions: Soften gelatine in 3 tablespoons grape juice.
Set aside. Cook washed cranberries and remaining grape juice, slowly, until tender.
Remove and stir in sugar substitute and gelatine.
Chill before serving.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems.
Drain caps.
Finely chop stems. Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion, pepperoni, green pepper, garlic and chopped mushroom stems.
Cook until vegetables are tender but not brown.
Add cracker crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper; mix well.
Stir in broth.
Spoon stuffing into caps, rounding on top.
Place caps in shallow baking pan with about 1/4 inch of water covering bottom of pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for about 25 minutes.
Extra filling can be heated and served on crackers.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350° and butter a casserole.
Cut or break bread into small pieces into baking dish.
Beat until fluffy the eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour over bread. Place casserole in shallow pan of water and bake for 1 hour or until knife test comes out clean.

title: icing for pig lickin cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and put between layers and cover cake completely.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: Separate lobster tails and claws.
In heavy kettle, heat oil; add onion, celery and garlic.
Cook until golden.
Add parsley, tomatoes, bouillon and wine.
Season with salt, thyme, paprika, saffron, fennel and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp, scallops and lobster.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion; drain grease, mix together all ingredients, then add beans.
Place in a covered baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add onion and cook over moderate heat until onion is soft.
Add mushrooms; cover pan and cook several minutes.
Remove mixture from heat and blend flour.
Add stock slowly; bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in cream.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf magnifico
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 c. of the sauce, beef, bread crumbs, onion, and egg.

title: mini-reubens
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread each slice of bread with 1/2 teaspoon each of butter and mustard.
Place two slices of corned beef on each slice.
Add a heaping teaspoonful of sauerkraut.
Top with a piece of cheese.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cut, if desired, in half and serve hot.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oleo and eggs.
Add soda, salt, cinnamon and flour.
Add nuts and apples.
Bake in 8-inch square pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: to prepare country ham
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain fruits and add water to make 1 3/4 c. liquid.
Bring to a boil and pour over Jello.
Add 1 1/2 c. cold water.
Refrigerate until mushy, then add fruits.

title: salmon mousse(serves 6; first course on lettuce and 12 as appetizer)
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice and 1/3 cup water over gelatin in a blender.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Whirl for 30 seconds, adding boiling water.
Add the rest of ingredients, whirling until smooth. Pour into Pam sprayed mold.
Chill until firm.
Remove from mold onto serving dish.

title: aaron's fast four layer cake
directions: Mix together walnuts, flour and butter (melted).
Pat on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Let cool completely.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and half of the whipped cream. Spread on first layer.
Mix milk and pudding. Spread on second layer.
Put remaining whipped cream on top. Grate chocolate Hershey bar to sprinkle on top of cake for decoration. Refrigerate for a couple
of hours.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Layer fruit in a large glass bowl in order given.
Spoon orange juice concentrate over top.
Cover and chill 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Makes 10 servings.

title: butter ball cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except jelly, in a bowl and blend well.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Break off small pieces of dough and roll into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets and make an indentation with your thumb in the center of each cookie.
Fill with 1/2 teaspoon jelly.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool on a rack.

title: nacho supreme taco dip
directions: 1st Layer:
Mashed beans mixed with cream cheese.

title: "chip-eze"
directions: Split each piece of pita bread into two separate round pieces. Spread butter over each piece.
Tear buttered bread into bite-sized pieces.
Spread them out on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle your salty topping over the pieces of bread.
Toast them under the broiler until desired crispness.

title: tuna delight
directions: With a pat of butter or margarine, grease an 8 x 8 or a
9 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Mix tuna fish and potato chips in a bowl.
Add a can of mushroom soup and the milk and mix well.
Add sharp Cheddar cheese and/or chopped onion, if desired.
Pour the tuna fish mixture into the baking dish and bake for about 1 hour in a 325°
oven.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all together.
Put in refrigerator.
Best if made 1 or 2 days ahead.
Enjoy!
Gets sweeter as raisins plump.
If you use fat-free mayo, you might have to add more sugar.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and rice - veggie main dish
directions: Wash and trim fat and skin off chicken parts.
Saute the chicken parts in a heavy 4-quart pot or deep frying pan.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Place in large cake dish on top of crust, 9 ounces of Cool Whip (1+ cup), powdered sugar and cream cheese, softened.
Mix chocolate pudding with milk.
Place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Put remaining Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with pecans, if desired.

title: christmas punch
directions: Keep orange juice undiluted.
Mix all ingredients in punch bowl.
Chill. Yields 4 quarts.

title: grilled shrimp my way
directions: You will also need small wooden skewers.

title: golden potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; chill, then peel and grate into large bowl.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, combine butter and cheese.
Stir occasionally until almost melted.
Remove from heat. Blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper; pour over potatoes. Mix and pour into casserole.
Spread butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups together.
Layer broccoli, chicken and plain croutons until all are used.
Spread soup mixture on top of layers.
Sprinkle a few more croutons and cheese on top and slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° to 375° to heat through.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Blend tomatoes briefly in food processor. Combine tomatoes, egg, oatmeal and soup mix.
Mix well, then add ground beef.
Mix thoroughly.
Place into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 70 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before slicing.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Preheat oven 400 degrees.
Cream together butter and sugar. Add egg and beat well.
Add persimmons and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to batter and mix well.
Stir in raisins and chopped nuts.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Boil vinegar, salt and sugar; let stand until cool and pour over mixture of other ingredients and let stand until cool.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in a 4-cup glass measure.
Blend well.
Place in microwave oven.
Cook on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Pause and stir until blended.
Cook again on half power 1 1/2 minutes.
Blend in vanilla.
Briskly stir with wire whisk until clear and shiny.
Refrigerate until cool.
Sauce will thicken as it stands.
Serve over ice cream, chocolate cake, fruit or dip pound cake or fruit.
Makes 1 cup.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello with boiling water in bowl.
When completely dissolved, fold in strawberries with juice, drained pineapple and bananas.
Add miniature marshmallows.

title: chinese vegetables
directions: Use pan with tight fitting lid.
Cut up and cook bacon until limp in pan.
Add remaining ingredients and steam 15 minutes over medium heat.
Do not add liquid.
No need to stir.
Leave lid on the entire 15 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: In a wok or deep skillet on medium heat, fry ground beef until light brown.
Add onion and carrots. Cook about 5 minutes.
Add cooked rice, green peas, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook another 5 minutes.
Transfer into serving dish. Beat eggs and fry in medium-hot pan, moving side to side to make a thin layer.
Remove from pan; dice and sprinkle on top of rice. Garnish with chopped scallions.

title: delightful fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, blend the fruit cocktail, pineapple, strawberries, mandarin oranges, banana and cottage cheese together.
Place into 6 individual dessert dishes.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Top each with lite Cool Whip and serve.

title: chocolate filling
directions: Mix cornstarch with cold water.
Add sugar and boiling water to chocolate; boil 3 minutes.
Add starch mixture and cook.
Cool. Add vanilla.
Excellent on yellow cake!

title: "no peek" chicken
directions: Mix rice, mushroom soup, parsley flakes and water together. Pour in well buttered casserole dish or pan (9 x 13-inch).
Lay chicken on top.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Seal tightly in foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/4 hours.
No peek!!

title: sugar-free dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers and margarine and pat in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Process or blend vanilla pudding, skim milk and cream cheese and pour into chilled crust.
When set, slice fresh fruit on top. Very healthy, tasty dessert.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks; add milk.
Add flour to make a stiff batter. Add melted butter and salt.
Add baking powder.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a well greased hot waffle iron.
Makes 6.
One or 2 tablespoons sugar may be added, if desired.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, salt and soda.
Add flour mixture gradually to the creamed mixture.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 425° for about 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 6 dozen.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In a saucepan, mix reserved juice, 1/2 cup water and lemon juice.
Heat to boiling. Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Stir thoroughly to break up cranberry sauce, then add to gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate until mixture starts to set.
Stir in pineapple, celery and nuts.
Pour into a 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked sweet and sour brussels sprouts
directions: Arrange sprouts in shallow baking dish.
Blend all ingredients, except cheese. Pour mixture over sprouts.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add salt and sugar while beating.
Beat until forms stiff peaks.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Put in 350° oven and turn oven off.
Do not open oven for at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk over low heat. Combine 1/3 cup milk, cake mix and margarine and mix well.
Press half of this mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle cup of nuts and chocolate bits over crust and add caramel mixture.
Top with teaspoonful of remaining cake mixture. Press into caramel mixture.
Add remaining walnuts, pressing them into top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate. Makes 2 dozen bars.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, bits and oleo.
Mix in Chex. Toss in powdered sugar.
Keeps well in covered container.

title: miniature party quiche
directions: Note:
Recipe makes about 7 to 8 dozen using miniature tart pans.

title: orange cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs together until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder together.
Add the sifted dry ingredients alternately with the buttermilk and orange juice.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake in oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Ice while hot with Orange Topping.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and syrup, creaming constantly.
Add the salt to the eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Then add eggs to first mixture.
Add the vanilla and broken pecan meats and pour into a 9-1/2-inch pie pan lined with unbaked pastry.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: long boy cheeseburger
directions: In a 2-quart mixing bowl, combine everything except cheese and rolls.
Cut rolls in half lengthwise.
Spread equal parts of beef mixture on roll halves.
Place on a cookie sheet.

title: low-fat dessert
directions: Tear angel food cake apart in small pieces.
Mix jello (dry) with 1 carton Cool Whip and the cake.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam. Pour cake mixture into pan.
Let set overnight in refrigerator. Pour out of pan and ice with other carton of Cool Whip.
Place strawberries on top of cake.

title: mama nipper's hot tamales
directions: Mix ground beef, sausage and chili mix well.
Shape into small logs, approximately 1 1/2 inches wide and 2 1/2 inches long.
Then mix corn meal, shortening and milk to make mixture.
Add meat mixture when corn meal mixture is wrapped in tamale papers; tie each end.
Bring to boil and cook for 1 hour.

title: lillian wright's lemon pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, 1 1/4 cups water and butter.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Add cornstarch blended with remaining water. Cook slowly until clear, about 8 minutes.
Add 6 tablespoons lemon juice and rind.
Cook about 2 minutes.
Slowly add egg yolks beaten with milk and bring to boil.
Cool.
Pour into baked shell. Spread with meringue made of egg whites, 6 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: *Ro-Tel is a can of tomatoes and green chilies, found in the can vegetable section of grocery store.

title: strawberry brownies
directions: Mix milk, pudding and water and chill 5 minutes.
Add Cool Whip.
Put on top of 9 x 13-inch pan of brownies and put strawberries on Cool Whip mixture.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Bake and cool pie shell.
Mix pudding with milk, let set a few minutes.
Fold marshmallows into Cool Whip.
Add to pudding mixture.
Slice in bananas and put into shell.
Chill at least 3 to 4 hours.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Toss and brown sausage; drain.
Tenderize bell pepper, onion and celery in a little butter.
Boil rice and soup mix in water for 7 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Add egg yolks, pineapple juice, sugar and vinegar in a saucepan and cook on low heat, stirring until pudding forms.
Let cool and add chopped pineapple, marshmallows and whipped cream. Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Blend ingredients thoroughly.
Roll into small balls and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: lemon delight
directions: Combine margarine, flour, sugar and nuts.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Singe ribs on grill for 5 minutes on each side.
Take off the grill.
Arrange meat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Use a small pan for a few ribs, or a larger one for company.) Cover the meat with the sauce.
Add water to make sure the meat is covered with liquid. Place pan on the grill for 1 hour.
Turn the ribs over after 30 minutes.
The meat wil be so tender, you can cut it with a fork.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine margarine and cheese in bowl.
Mix flour, salt and red pepper with hands.
Add rice cereal; mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Press with fork to flatten.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Yield: 6 dozen.

title: fiesta rice
directions: In skillet over medium heat, saute the onion in butter until tender.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Stir in the next 9 ingredients. Divide between two ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover.
Sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind the squash, onions and peppers.
Sprinkle with the salt; let set overnight.
In the morning, rinse well and drain.
Combine the vinegar, sugar, pepper, nutmeg, dry mustard and celery seed. Add all ingredients in large pan; simmer for 3 minutes.
Seal hot in jars.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: mediterranean pasta salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Stir in tomatoes, oil, parsley, basil and garlic.
Toss gently with pasta, olives and onions. Cover and chill 2 hours. Before serving, add cheese, salt and pepper.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend butter, sugar and egg.
Add baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add flour.
Mix by hand.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in an 8-inch pan.

title: cajun pasta
directions: Melt two Sticks of butter, add chicken bouillon cubes and mix in the Paul Prudhommes Seafood Magic (or Emeril Essence).
Add the Chopped Parsley.
Keep on medium heat.
Prepare the Alfredo sauce (as directed on package) in a separate pan.
Add the three cups of milk and 2 teaspoons of butter to the Knorr Alfredo sauce mix. Dice your chicken into bite sized chunks and brown in a pan with butter.
After chicken is done, add to the seasoned butter mixture and simmer on medium heat.
Brown mushrooms in butter until they are soft.
Add the seasoned chicken to the butter/mushroom mixture. Keep on medium heat.
Keep mixing until all the seasons blend together.
Combine the butter/seasoned chicken mixture and the Alfredo sauce along with the chopped red and green bell peppers with the bacon bits into pan and let it set on medium heat.
Boil your linguine in water until done.
Drain water.
Toss in your Cajun mixture with the linguine in one big pan.
Add the cooked shrimp and crabmeat at the very end.
Last of all, add the cracked pepper.
Let simmer for approximately 15 minutes.
Smell the aroma of the dish and prepare for your taste buds to jump with excitement and that's before you taste it.
I bet you can't wait and sneak a sample before you serve it.
ENJOY!!!!!
This dish will tease your taste buds by making you think you are sitting at a fancy restaurant.
Takes approximately 1 hour for preparation and cooking time.
Best served when it's been cooking for 1 1/2 to 2 Hours. (Could serve up to 8.)
tags: Packets of Knorr Alfredo Sauce Mix

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Simmer for 1 hour in 3 quarts water. Add all ingredients except kielbasa and cheese.
Simmer another hour.
Add kielbasa and simmer 1 more hour.
Serve hot, sprinkled with Parmesan.

title: wassail
directions: Simmer cloves and cinnamon stick in 1 cup of cider for 2 hours. Strain and pour into mixture of cider, pineapple juice and cranberry juice.
Serve hot.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: chinese slaw
directions: Combine cole slaw mix with peas. toss with oil, sugar, poppy seed, dry mustard, salt, grated onion and vinegar. Sprinkle with roasted peanuts.

title: avocado filled with shrimp and pineapple
directions: Peel avocados and halve lengthwise.
Remove pits.
Rub with lemon juice to preserve color.
Cut shrimp into 1/4-inch pieces. Toss with celery and pineapple.
Blend in sour cream, onion salt and salt.
Pile salad mixture into avocados; sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon Swiss cheese.
Chill 1/2 hour before serving.
Serves 4.

title: pig in a blanket
directions: Cut hot dogs in half.
Split hot dog lengthwise and place cheese in hot dog.
Cut crescent rolls in half.
Roll hot dog in crescent roll.
Bake by directions on crescent roll package.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chop chicken. Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients.

title: thumbprints
directions: Whip cream until stiff; sweeten to taste or leave unsweetened. Put through a pastry tube and make rosettes on a piece of wax paper the size of a cookie sheet.
Put in freezer overnight until hard.

title: quick clam linguini
directions: Cook linguini according to package, omitting salt.
Drain linguini and set aside.
Saute garlic in butter in a large skillet. Drain clams and add juice to skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Cook over medium heat for 7 minutes.
Add clams and cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until cheese melts.
Pour sauce over linguini; add parsley and toss gently.
Serves 4.

title: jiffy pie
directions: In a deep-dish baking pan, melt butter. Mix all other ingredients and pour batter into the melted butter pan. Place fruit of your choice in last. Cook until brown, about 40 to 45 minutes in an oven that is 250° to 300°.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, oil and eggs until well blended. Add 7-Up.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool to warm and apply topping.

title: cherry fluff dessert
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and 1/4 cup melted butter. Pack this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Spread over the graham cracker crust. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Prepare 1 package of whipped topping mix and spread over nuts.
Let sit in refrigerator for 1/2 hour. Remove and spread cherry pie filling over top.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: cabbage, lettuce and potato salad dressing
directions: Mix cornstarch and water and add rest of ingredients.
Cook until like cream.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and work together the peanut butter and sugar until smooth.
Roll into balls; put in refrigerator overnight.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip peanut butter in chocolate and place on wax paper until cool.

title: ciara's hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Store in an air-tight container or a gallon jar.

title: broccoli roll-ups
directions: Cook broccoli.
Roll out biscuits 5 to 6 inches round.
Place 2 spears of broccoli and sprinkle ham on.
Fold biscuit in half and pinch edges.
Cook at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken & dumplings
directions: Wash and cut up hen in frying size pieces.
Salt and pepper each piece.
Place in 5 quart pan, cover with water, and cook until thickest piece (usually the breast) "flakes" or separates easily with fork, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
If using a pressure cooker (Presto cooker), add water up to 3/4 of chicken; cook for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender in oven.
Remove bones and chop coarsely.
Mix together the soups and sour cream.
Pour over chopped chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with poppy seed.
Top with cracker mixture.
Pour melted margarine over crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all together and store in sealed jars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and pull off bone.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Place chicken in dish and pour soup mixture over. Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken baked in sour cream
directions: Wash and dry chicken breasts.
Combine all ingredients, except margarine and crumbs.
Coat each chicken breast with sour cream mixture.
Cover and let stand in fridge overnight.
Roll in corn flake crumbs.
Arrange in baking dish.
Pour 1/2 of margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour last 1/2 of margarine over chicken and bake 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally, or cook in crock-pot 4 to 5 hours.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Cut up fruits.
Pour in cracker crumbs, pecans and condensed milk.
Melt butter and marshmallows; pour over all ingredients. Add vanilla.
Mix real well and pack in buttered tube pan. Refrigerate and wait 2 days before cutting.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Crumb together flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon and Crisco.
In another bowl, mix molasses with water and baking soda.
Divide liquid mixture into unbaked pie crusts, then quickly sprinkle crumbs over the 2 pies.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: cheese filled manicotti
directions: Cook shells as directed on package.
Drain, rinse with cold water.
Next, combine Ricotta cheese, mozzarella cheese, 3/4 cup of parmesan cheese, the eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into cooked shells.

title: fritos dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add all ingredients and mix.
Serve with Fritos chips.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream peanut butter and butter.
Add vanilla and mix well. Begin to work in 10x sugar in small amounts.
Keep adding and working in 10x sugar until mixture can be easily rolled into balls.
Refrigerate balls until firm.

title: chocolate angel pie in meringue crust
directions: Beat until foamy the egg whites, salt and cream of tartar. Add sugar 2 tablespoons at a time and beat.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Spoon into lightly greased 8-inch pie pan.
Make a nest-like shell.
Build up sides 1/2-inch above edge of pan.
Bake slow and cool.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Bake by directions on box.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) round pans. When cold, slice each one through the middle, making 4 layers.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Barely cover chicken with water and cook on stove top until done (about 25 minutes).
Preserve liquid.
Cut up chicken and place in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine chicken broth soup and reserved liquid to make 3 cups.
Pour one cup over cut up chicken. Mix cream of chicken soup and melted margarine and put over chicken and dressing casserole ingredients in casserole.
Prepare dressing mix according to directions except use 2 cups of the reserved chicken broth instead of water.
Put dressing over chicken and bake at 350°, uncovered, about 40 minutes or until browned and bubbling.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: christmas crispy drops
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well. Blend in vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: poppy seed bundt cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat 5 minutes with mixer.
Place batter in greased Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let rest in the pan on a rack 15 minutes.
If you want to make a glaze for the top, use powdered sugar and butter and add cream sherry, if desired.

title: lemon blueberry meringue pie
directions: In medium size mixing bowl, blend together condensed milk, lemon juice, lemon peel and eggs until thickened.
Fold in blueberries.
Turn into pie shell.

title: fast cake dessert
directions: Spread pie filling in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dry jello and 1 cup sugar together; spread evenly over fruit mixture.
Spread box of dry yellow cake mix over that.

title: mama's old fashioned meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain off excess grease.
Cover top with ketchup; bake for 10 minutes.

title: escalloped pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients together; pour into greased casserole.
Pour melted margarine and bread crumbs on top of mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Great with ham.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain and rinse.
Mix all ingredients in large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: christmas bread
directions: Blend together margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually blend into first mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts, cherries, chocolate and raisins.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool.
Spread with icing.

title: minestrone
directions: Choose a large stockpot.

Put in oil, butter and onion and cook over medium-low heat. Add the other fresh vegetables, one at a time, stirring once or twice and cooking each new addition several minutes before adding the next one. After adding the cabbage, cook about 6 minutes, then add the broth, tomatoes and their juice and a little bit of salt.
Cook slowly, covered, for at least 3 hours.
If you see it's becoming too thick, add a bit more water to your taste.
Fifteen minutes before the soup is done, add the canned cannellini beans.

title: pie crust
directions: Crumble all ingredients together with a fork until smooth. Roll out on floured board with rolling pin.

title: orange cake
directions: Follow directions on back of cake mix box.
Cook orange juice and sugar for 5 minutes.
Juice will not get thick, will get steamy and hot.
Beat together yellow cake mix, water, vegetable oil or butter, eggs and orange Jell-O.
Beat together for about 2 minutes. Grease and flour desired pan to cook.
Bake at 350° for 33 to 38 minutes.
Let cool; pour hot, steamy orange syrup over cake. Spread evenly.
Cool, then ready to eat!

title: mustard dip
directions: Mix all together in order given.
Serve with corn chips or beef sticks.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all, 1 cup nuts, together.
Chill and roll in remaining nuts after shaping.
Refrigerate well.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and onions, cook in a little water for 5 minutes. Drain water off. Dice cheese into small cubes. Mix cheese, potatoes and onion. Put in buttered casserole. Mix soup, milk and parsley. Pour over potatoes. Crumble crackers and sprinkle over top, dot with butter. Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees, covered. Remove lid last 15 minutes so top can brown.

title: delicious chicken salad(prep time:  30 minutes; serves 4)
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt.
Heat water, sherry and soy sauce in large skillet to simmer.
Add chicken; cover and simmer 10 minutes, turning once, until chicken is cooked through (do not overcook chicken or it will become dry).
Remove chicken to cutting board to cool.

title: junk yard salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
Take out of freezer and serve when solid.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine and form into small balls and bake on ungreased pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: barbecue sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef or chuck with onion.
Put meat mixture in crock-pot.
Mix all the other ingredients together and add to meat mixture. Simmer in crock-pot 2 to 3 hours or longer if desired. Serve on buns.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix sugar, oil, chocolate and vanilla.
Mix in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Shape into small balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until almost no indentation remains when touched.

title: cheese stuffed vegetables
directions: In medium bowl with mixer at low speed, beat soup into cream cheese until well blended.
Beat in lemon juice, garlic, summer savory leaves and pepper.
Cover; refrigerate 4 hours.
Using spoon or decorating tube, stuff cheese mixture into tomatoes. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: italian herb potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place in microwave-safe dish.
Drizzle with olive oil and mix well.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High 7 to 9 minutes or until tender.
Mix halfway through cooking time. Sprinkle with cheese and microwave on High 1 minute longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turkey or chicken dressing
directions: Cook sausage; mix sausage and croutons in a bowl.
Cook celery and onions in sausage juice.
Add 1/2 cup water to steam it, then add parsley.
Cook until almost tender, then mix with sausage and croutons, then add green pepper (chopped), 2 eggs, salt, pepper and sage, then dissolve bouillon in water or pan drippings to make dressing moist.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones.
In 5-quart pot, add chicken broth.
Add water.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Bring all these to a boil.
Add egg noodles.
Cook until potatoes and noodles are done.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter
in
a 9 x 12-inch pan in oven.
Add graham cracker crumbs and spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Add each item in order listed; add Eagle Brand milk last.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal picnic bars
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; stir.
Add oleo and eggs; blend.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan and bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk, strawberries and lemon juice together. Pour into pie crusts.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a food processor, work oatmeal until powder-like.
Also, take 2 ounces of chocolate bits and blend in processor until powder-like; set aside with oatmeal.
With electric mixer, cream the butter and the sugars until light.
Add the egg and vanilla. With lowest speed, add flour, salt, baking soda, oatmeal and chocolate bit mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add 6 ounces chocolate bits.
Spoon walnut size balls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter over low heat in layer pans (9 x 1 1/2-inches).

Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter. Arrange pineapple halves, cherries and pecans over sugar mixture. Prepare cake mix as directed on package; pour half the batter (about 2 1/2 cups) evenly over fruit in pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: blueberry jam
directions: Mash berries with water and sugar.
Bring to rolling boil; remove from heat.
Add the lemon jello; mix well.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes 1 pint.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Blend all ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch or two 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Cool completely and frost.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Bake chicken, covered, 15 minutes in a preheated 425° oven. Drain tomatoes; combine with cornstarch, oregano and pepper sauce. Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour hot sauce over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 4.

title: frozen boston nut
directions: Mix peanut butter and syrup.
Add Cocoa Krispies.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread ice cream evenly over Cocoa Krispies. Drizzle with Hershey's chocolate.
Add crushed peanuts on top when serving.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown chops in frying pan.
Drain.
In baking dish, slice as many potatoes as needed.
Place pork chops on potatoes and cover with mushrooms and onion soup mix.
Pour water over meat.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix hamburger, egg, salt and pepper.
Make into patties.
In a frying pan heat 3 tablespoons oil and brown patties on both sides. In a greased baking dish, place patties, to this add milk and cream of mushroom soup (thoroughly mixed).
Sprinkle top with pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and salt.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil only 2 minutes.
Place Marshmallow Creme in a large bowl.
Pour hot syrup, all at once, in Marshmallow Creme.
Beat until candy loses its gloss.
Add nuts.
Drop by the spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and canned milk; add Cool Whip and vanilla.
(Add bananas or strawberries unless you want vanilla ice cream).
Pour into 4-quart ice cream freezer and add whole milk to fill line.
After attaching lid and top of freezer, fill with rock salt and ice.
Should be finished in 20 to 30 minutes.
(If electric freezer stops within first 10 to 15 minutes, add a little water to ice).

title: jello mold
directions: Melt butter; mix with chopped pretzels.
Press into bottom of 4-quart oblong Pyrex dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Set aside and cool.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until light. Add beaten egg yolks and vanilla. Beat until thoroughly blended. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk. Stir in blackberry jam. Fold in egg whites, beaten. Pour batter into 10-inch tube pan that has been lined on bottom with waxed paper and greased. Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes. Increase heat to 350° and cook until tested done with cake tester.

title: honey lemon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
In a bowl beat butter, honey and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolk, lemon peel and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in dry ingredients until mixed well. Divide dough in half.
Shape into 8-inch logs.
Slice logs into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place on cookie sheets 1/2 inch apart. Bake for 7 minutes.
Let stand for 1 minute; then cool.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: basil pesto sauce
directions: Process all ingredients in a blender or food processor until smooth, stopping occasionally to scrape down sides.
Pesto can be served immediately or spooned into ice-cube trays and frozen. Wrap cubes tightly in freezer bags and store in freezer up to 6 months.
Makes 2 cups or 16 (2-tablespoon-size) cubes.
Pesto can stand alone as a dip and also is good as a spread for pizzas and sandwiches.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass).
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with other ingredients; press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned. Cool before cutting.

title: apple carrot casserole
directions: Place carrots in a pie dish.
Top with apple pie filling. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° (or in the microwave) until hot and bubbly.

title: party cheesecake
directions: Place paper liners in 24 muffin cups; put 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla; beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour enough filling into muffin cups to fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly or refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, spoon pie filling on top of cheesecake.
Top with whipped cream.
Makes 24 cheesecakes.

title: john's dressing for cole slaw
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and process until well blended. (It may be thin when first made, but will thicken in refrigerator.)
It keeps well.

title: vegetable-beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onions into a large Dutch oven, then finish adding lemon pepper, garlic, black pepper, green beans, lima beans, tomatoes, cabbage, corn, okra and water.
Cook on stove top on medium for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Serve it with cornbread.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar.
Add flour alternately with eggs.
Beat well.
Add whipping cream straight from carton.
Add flavoring.
Beat well.
Put in cold oven.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in tube pan at 325°.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in butter.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt. Add sugar.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles; drain.
Mix onion, cream cheese and sour cream.
Place in baking dish:
1 layer noodles, 1 layer onion mixture and 1 layer meat.
Continue until all ingredients are used.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Beat egg yolks. Add vanilla and 1/2 of the sugar. Beat egg whites until frothy. Add cream of tartar. Beat until stiff. Fold egg mixture into whites. Fold flour, salt and remaining sugar into mixture. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in tube pan.

title: salad supreme
directions: Dissolve cherry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; add cherry pie filling to hot Jell-O, put in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Chill until partially set.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Beat together cream cheese and mayonnaise, gradually add lemon Jell-O, stir in undrained pineapple, fold in whipped cream and marshmallows.
Spread over cherry Jell-O mixture.
If desired, sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts over top.
Chill until set.

title: fox hunters pie
directions: Place chips and pecans in bottom of crust.
Blend the rest and pour over chips and nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Allow to cool.

title: butterhorns
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into horns.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana-walnut muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, nuts, soda and salt in large bowl.
Mix bananas, butter, egg and milk together and add to dry ingredients. Mix slightly to blend.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: monster cookies
directions: Use a large bowl for mixing.
Mix in order given.
Dough can be frozen and baked as needed.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Makes several dozen. Very good!

title: clyde jr. corn fritters
directions: Drain corn; set aside.
Sift together the salt and baking powder.
Blend milk and egg; gradually add to the dry ingredients. Stir in the corn; mix well.

title: floretta flynn's dumplings
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Mix in shortening with fork. Blend well.
Add milk to make stiff dough.
Divide into 3 or 4 parts.
Roll out thin on floured surface. Cut into narrow strips. Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add dumplings one strip at a time, until all have been added.
Place chicken that has been removed from bones on top of dumplings.
Stir slightly to keep from sticking.
Cook over low heat 10 to 12 minutes.
Turn off heat and let stand until ready to serve.
Serve hot.

title: kelsey's favorite banana bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Blend eggs, sugar and oil well.
Stir flour, vanilla and mashed bananas.
Add all to the flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2. Enjoy.

title: 1-2-4 cut-out cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Add flour, about 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Vanilla may be added along with the flour.
Roll out portions of the dough, using a mixture of flour and powdered sugar on the rolling surface.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and frost.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: baked fruit
directions: Place peaches and pears in baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and cook until thick.

title: pepper steaks
directions: Wash and pare medium potatoes.
Make a hole through each with an apple corer and force a link sausage or two (depending on size) into each cavity.
Place potatoes in baking dish and bake in oven at 425° for 45 minutes or until tender, basting with sausage drippings several times during baking.
A slice of bacon can be placed over each potato, if desired.

title: parmesan delights
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, cover and chill (may be prepared in advance).
Preheat broiler; spread one heaping teaspoonful of mayonnaise mixture on each piece of bread.
Place on baking sheet and broil until lightly browned, 2 or 3 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: medirnyk (honey cake)(international:  ukraine)
directions: Bring honey just to a boil.
Cool.
Cream together brown sugar and butter.
Slowly beat in egg yolks, then honey.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder into mixing bowl.
Cut margarine into flour mixture until it looks like coarse meal.
Stir in raisins.

Combine buttermilk, egg and baking soda; stir into flour mixture just enough to moisten dry ingredients. Turn onto floured board; knead lightly until dough is smooth. Shape into a ball and place in a greased 2-quart casserole.

title: broccoli and cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil potatoes until done.
While potatoes are cooking, add salt and pepper to taste.
In another pot, mix broccoli and cheese soup with 1/4 cup of mix and stir until creamy.
Add a little more milk if needed to keep the soup from getting thick.
Keep it a little loose and creamy.
Pour potatoes in casserole dish and pour mixture on top.
Put in oven for 30 minutes.

title: sugarplum divinity
