directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook until candy thermometer registers 260° or until it reaches the very hard ball stage.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour hot mixture very slowly over egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue beating until mixture becomes very stiff and loses its glossy appearance.
Beat a few strokes by hand to improve texture.
Add vanilla and drop by large spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Decorate with slivers of gum drops by pressing cut edges to candy.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: poor boy stew
directions: Place onion, potatoes and carrots in large pan filled 2/3 with water.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes. Bring to boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: sally's pizza dough
directions: Combine yeast
and
water
in
a
small
bowl, then add sugar. Let
stand
for 5 minutes.
Add 2 cups flour, salt and oil.
Mix until
smooth.
Add
additional
1 cup flour as you knead the dough.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Smash out or roll out to make
pizza crust.
Put
crust
onto a greased pan and add pizza
sauce, shredded
Mozzarella
and/or Cheddar cheese and desired toppings. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: elephant ears
directions: Heat together, but don't boil the milk, sugar and shortening, until shortening is melted.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Stir in flour, 2 cups at a time, beating until smooth after each addition.
Put in greased bowl; cover with damp cloth and let rise until double, about 30 minutes.
Dust hands with flour; pinch off pieces of dough about the size of a golf ball.
Stretch each ball into a thin 6 to 8-inch circle.
Have oil at 350°.
Drop stretched dough, one at a time, in the hot oil and fry until it rises to the surface; turn and fry the other side until light brown.
Drain on absorbent paper and sprinkle generously with sugar mixture.

title: king ranch enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken in a small amount of lightly salted water until tender.
Bone and cut into pieces.
Blend together the 2 cans of soup, tomatoes and green chilies and chicken broth.
In a 2 1/2-quart greased casserole, place a layer of chicken, 1/2 of the tortillas (cut into large pieces), 1/2 onion, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 soup mixture.
Repeat the layers, ending with grated cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix sugar eggs, butter, vanilla and cream cheese.
Gradually add flour and 7-Up.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: althea walter's homemade chili
directions: Brown beef and onion with salt and pepper.
Add flour and chili powder.
Stir until well blended.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Cook on low for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add chili beans.
Cook 30 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: southern plantation cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: new orleans bread pudding with sauce
directions: Soak bread in milk and crush until well mixed. Add eggs, sugar, vanilla and raisins.
Stir well.
Pour melted oleo into bottom of baking pan or casserole.
Add other ingredients.
Bake until firm.

title: sweet 'n sour chops
directions: Brown chops (both sides) in skillet.
Season to taste.
Drain any excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir.
Pour over chops; cover.
Simmer in skillet 45 to 50 minutes or until done. Remove chops.
Boil sauce and pour over chops which were removed to serving platter.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine apples, 5 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon. Set aside. Mix with a mixer the flour, sugar, oil, eggs, salt, vanilla, baking powder and juice. Stir in walnuts. Grease and flour tube pan.
Alternate apples and butter.
Use syrup, too. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini meat dish(by brenda ross)
directions: In large skillet brown ground beef, push to one side and remove all but 2 tablespoons of fat.
Add rice, squash and onion. Cook and stir until slightly browned.
Stir in tomatoes, water, garlic salt, pepper and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until done.
Put cheese over top of mixture and melt. Serve.

title: fruit sheet cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients listed about 3 minutes (batter will be thick).
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (flour and greased or sprayed with Pam).
Open fruit filling and put on top of dough.
Cut into cake with knife; swirl like for marble cake.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cover with glaze.

title: ziti with scallops and peppers
directions: Cook ziti according to directions.
Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in skillet and saute peppers for 5 minutes.
Add wine and cook another minute.
Add the scallops, basil, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over high heat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Toss the ziti with 1 tablespoon of olive oil.
Cover ziti with scallop mixture.

title: whatever salad
directions: Layer as listed (bacon on bottom).
Do not stir until ready to serve.
Cover with Saran Wrap; refrigerate up to 4 hours or more. Stir just before serving.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken.
Save broth.
Cool and cut breasts into chunks. Put in broth.
Add cream of chicken soup, noodles, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add 1 stick oleo.
Cook until noodles are done.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture, blending thoroughly.
Add nuts. Form dough into two rolls; wrap in wax paper.
Store in refrigerator.
Slice and bake as needed at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: french boiled dinner
directions: Put ham in pot.
Bring to a boil.
Add carrots, onions, salt and pepper.
Cover over medium heat until done.
Add potatoes, then when they are done, add cabbage, cut up.
Cook until done.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Day Before Serving:
Cook spaghetti.
Don't use salt or oil. Rinse in cold water and drain.
Marinate overnight in 4 ounces of Italian dressing.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift together sugar, salt and flour.
Gradually add Crisco, lemon juice and milk.
Mix all ingredients together; mix well. Add 1 egg yolk.
Place between wax paper to roll.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until light and blend with the sugar and flour.
Add melted margarine, then milk, vanilla and coconut.
Put in uncooked pastry and bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Bake at 325° (no top).

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, salsa, Tabasco and lemon juice and spread into bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add lettuce, green pepper, onion, tomatoes, cheese, olives and jalapeno peppers.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: my mother's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, draining off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients (except for spaghetti) and simmer slowly, stirring often, for about 30 minutes to an hour (more if you have time, but don't let it cook more than 1 1/2 hours).
Serve spooned over the cooked spaghetti on a platter.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix separately 2 tablespoons sugar with 1 tablespoon cinnamon.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and pumpkin; mix.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use a Bundt pan or 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut onions into 3/4-inch slices.
In a 12-inch skillet, cook onions in butter or margarine until tender. Sprinkle with salt, sugar and pepper.
Add vermouth and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook 3 minutes.
Transfer onion mixture to a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs, paprika and melted butter.
Sprinkle over cheese. Bake for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: deer meat log
directions: Mix up first 5 ingredients of seasoning in a bowl.
Sift into meat and mix thoroughly.
Also gradually mix in liquid smoke and brown sugar.
Make sure all ingredients are mixed thoroughly.
Let set in a cool place for 24 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle almonds over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: magic cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a large casserole dish; put aside.
Mix all ingredients together and pour on top of melted margarine, but do not stir.
Pour a large can of peaches or other fruit pie filling on top of batter.
The dough will rise through the fruit to make a nice top crust.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix water, vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt, pepper and cayenne. Add lemon and onion. Simmer 20 minutes. Add catsup and Worcestershire sauce; bring to boil.

title: macaroni-meat loaf casserole
directions: Brown ground meat in butter.
Add vegetable soup and water. Bring to boil.
Add garlic salt, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard.
Mix in cooked elbow macaroni.
Pour into a 2-quart greased baking dish.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with tomato slices and grated cheese.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked mostaccioli
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain. Boil noodles and drain. Dice green pepper and onion.
Mix the two together.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water gradually.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and salt.
Good for bread pudding and other desserts.

title: magic french fudge
directions: Melt chocolate morsels in double boiler until smooth in texture.
Add vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Add nuts. Refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add salt and bananas, then add soda and flour.
Mix until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream together until smooth the oleo and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat in.
Add alternately small amounts of milk and wafers.
Mix in.
Add and mix in coconut and pecans.
Bake at 275° in ungreased angel food tube cake pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: jimmy carter's peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips;
add peanut butter.
Mix and add salted peanuts. Can use pecans.
Drop on buttered foil or waxed paper.

title: white chocolate candied fruit
directions: Line 8 X 8 pan with waxed paper (make sure all sides are covered).
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add candied fruit and condensed milk.
Pour into pan and freeze about 30 minutes.
Cut into small pieces and place into candy paper cups.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all together.
Use all the juices in the cans.
Rinse out each bean can with 1/2 can water to soup.
Simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Freezes well.
Add more water for thinner soup.
You will need a 5 quart pot to cook this soup in or 2 smaller pots.
Recipe can be halved.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add beaten eggs and mix well. Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture, then stir in apples, vanilla and nuts.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix graham crackers (crushed) with sugar.
Put in pie shell with high sides.
If using for pumpkin mousse, then add melted butter.
Press with fork into sides.

title: potato-stuffed meat loaf
directions: In medium saucepan, add potatoes and cold water to cover. Partially cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until tender when pierced, 30 to 35 minutes.
Preheat oven to 325°. Line a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with a sheet of aluminum foil; allow foil to overlap in large nonstick skillet.
Heat oil.
Add cabbage and onion; saute until well browned, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: green eggs and ham
directions: Brown ham and onion.
Blend eggs and milk.
Add eggs and spinach to ham.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir until done. Sprinkle with cheese before serving.

title: chicken and barley soup
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot.
Bring to boil.
Reduce to simmer, cover and cook about 1 1/4 hours, stirring occasionally. Remove thighs, cool slightly, remove meat from bone and return to soup.
Discard bones.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons parsley and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve.

title: rice
directions: Place in casserole dish. Stir until butter melts. Cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: shrimp a la nino
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan over moderate heat, without letting it brown.
Add the flour and stir with a wire whisk until well blended.
Meanwhile, bring milk almost to a boil.
While stirring the butter and flour mixture, add the warm milk.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add Pernod liquor.
Peel and devein the shrimp. Add to the hot Pernod sauce.
Before serving, stir in fresh fennel.
Serve on a bed of orzo.
Braised fennel makes a nice accompaniment.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add the next 9 ingredients to the hamburger to make sauce.
Precook 9 lasagne noodles.
Put 1 tablespoon oil or butter in water to prevent sticking.
In an 8-inch pan arrange the ingredients in layers as follows.

title: dorothy's cabbage stew
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Season meat with black pepper, salt and chili powder.
In large pot, slice cabbage; bring to boil.
Add meat mixture, corn, tomatoes and mixed vegetables; simmer for about 20 minutes.
Cabbage should be crunchy, not too soft.

title: tex-mex jalapeno dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift together corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Add eggs, milk and shortening. Beat with rotary beater until smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) square baking pans.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer. Add meatballs or hamburger.

title: turkey meat loaf(yields 6 servings)
directions: Spray loaf pan.
Whisk eggs, milk and seasonings.
Combine all ingredients.
Turn into loaf pan; brush with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: apple-walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in oil and vanilla.
Mix and sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir into egg mixture alternately with apple-sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Let stand in pan until cool.
(I like a thin powdered sugar icing on top but you can leave without; a very rich, heavy, moist cake.)

title: quick party dessert
directions: Melt Hershey bars and baking chocolate in double boiler.
Cool slightly.
Fold into the cream which has been whipped.
Cut cake into 2 layers.
Ice between layers and on top, etc.
Refrigerate for at least 12 hours before serving.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add all remaining ingredients and stir until moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 5 minutes and remove from pans.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Saute chicken breasts.
Add each of the other ingredients, one at a time.
Cook this sauce down until it begins to thicken and serve.

title: croissants
directions: Cream butter with 1/3 cup flour.
Chill and roll out between 2 sheets of waxed paper into an oblong shape measuring 12 inches by 6 inches. Chill until ready to use.
Use very warm water (105° to 115°). Sprinkle yeast into water.
Let stand for a few minutes, then stir to dissolve.

title: chocolate marshmallow haystacks
directions: Melt chocolate in microwavable dish on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until "almost" melted.
Stir until completely melted.
Cool slightly.

title: green chili stew
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add a little water and cook pork slowly for 30 to 40 minutes or until cubes are done.
Drain.
Add flour to meat and stir to coat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until thickened and potatoes are done.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Prepare the vanilla pudding as directed (less 1/2 cup milk). Add the Cool Whip to the vanilla pudding (stir well).
Line the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch cake pan with whole graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 of the pudding mixture on top of crackers.
Lay a second layer of crackers on the pudding mixture.
Then pour the remaining pudding mixture on top of the crackers.
Lay another layer of crackers on top of the mixture.
Spread 1 can of chocolate icing on top of graham crackers.
Refrigerate to set.

title: holiday ribbon ring
directions: Dissolve strawberry flavor gelatin in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour 1 1/2 cups into 6-cup ring mold.
Chill until set, but not firm, about 15 minutes.
Chill remaining gelatin in bowl; gradually blend in 1/3 cup of the sour cream and spoon over gelatin in mold.
Chill until set, but not firm, about 15 minutes. Repeat with lime flavor gelatin, remaining 2 1/2 cups water and 1/3 cup sour cream, chilling dissolved gelatin before measuring and pouring into mold.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Unmold.
Makes 12 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon.
Add onion; saute.
Add potatoes and water.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add corn and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in milk, salt and pepper.
Heat slowly.

title: low-fat chicken enchiladas
directions: Remove tortillas from refrigerator; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
In nonstick skillet, melt margarine.
Cook onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in green chilies, sour cream and soup; mix well.
Reserve 3/4 cup sauce; set aside.
Stir in chicken and 1/2 cup cheese to remaining sauce in skillet.
Warm tortillas according to package directions.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture; roll up.
Place seam-side down in ungreased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In small bowl, combine reserved sauce and milk; spoon over rolled tortillas.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix oleo, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and add powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Spread on hot cake right away.

title: snow covered almond crescents
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat margarine, sugar and almond extract until well blended.
Add flour and salt; mix well until well blended.
Stir in oats and almonds.
Using level measuring tablespoonful, shape dough into crescents.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 14 to 17 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar over cookies. Store tightly covered.

title: mazetti
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Combine
with
remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole
dish
and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach icebox
directions: Crumble wafers coarsely in 9 x 9-inch dish.
Melt margarine and mix with eggs, sugar and flavoring; pour over wafers.
Put peaches on top of wafers and cover with Cool Whip.
Chill overnight; serve.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Chill dough; roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into shapes.
Place 1 inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake until when touched lightly with finger and no imprint remains at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
When cool, decorate as desired.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together; beat 4 minutes.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350° in 2 greased loaf pans.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
In a mixer bowl, cream honey and shortening with electric mixer.
Add milk and eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture and bananas alternately, beating after each addition.
Fold in nuts.
Turn batter into a lightly greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool. For easier slicing, wrap and store overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup, salad dressing, eggs, sharp Cheddar cheese and chopped onion.
Boil 1 small bag of chopped broccoli 5 minutes in salted water and drain well.
Mix with mixture and sprinkle with butter and Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (1/4 pound Ritz to 2 teaspoons butter).

title: taco salsa
directions: Cook to boiling, simmer until thick.
Stir often.
Stir in 1 large can tomato paste and simmer 5 to 10 more minutes.

title: muffins(note:  use a cast-iron muffin pan!)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and bake in greased muffin pan at 450°.
Split while hot!
Add butter and one "bit" of sugar to each muffin.
Delicious!

title: rice pudding
directions: Put all ingredients into a kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook until rice is done and pudding is thick and creamy, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: fruit punch with frozen fruit ring
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Mix sugar and 4 cups water.
Add fruit juice and fruit, then freeze to a slushy stage.
If left in freezer, remove and let thaw to slushy stage and add 4 to 6 bottles Sprite.
Add fruit ring, floating on top.
Serves 75 to 100.

title: sour cream mini-biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients in mixer bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until just blended.
Spoon into ungreased miniature muffin pans. Makes 18.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Flatten in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together the sugar, oil, eggs and carrots.
To this, add the flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; blend well.
Add the crushed pineapple, walnuts, raisins and vanilla.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan or 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
In second bowl, combine rest of ingredients.
Combine wet and dry ingredients. Spread in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more when center is done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and spread on top of potatoes. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Makes 1 gallon.
Can be frozen up to 1 month.

title: macadamia nut pie
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and corn syrup.
Stir in the nuts.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour mixture into pastry shell. Bake in a moderately slow 325° oven for 50 minutes or until crust is golden and center of pie is set.
Test by shaking gently.
Let cool and chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and slice squash and onion.
Add water and cook until tender.
Drain well.
Put in casserole dish.
Add soup, undiluted. Add cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Top with cracker crumbs and pats of butter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: sweet tomato sauce
directions: Simmer together for 4 hours (at least).
Place in hot jars and seal.
Great over beans, peas, French fries, etc.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, oleo and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift cocoa with flour three times.
Add vanilla, milk and flour.
Beat well.
Put cake in cold oven.
To start turn oven on to 300°.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.
Test with toothpick to see if done.
Bake in tube pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter. Cook broccoli then drain. Add mushrooms, soup, cheese, onions and 1/4 cup almonds. Sprinkle with remaining almonds and bread crumbs. Bake at 325° until bubbling. Serves 8 to 10.

title: white-black walnut candy
directions: Cook sugar and half and half to soft ball stage.
Take from heat and add margarine, almond extract and salt.
Beat until cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in buttered dish.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Clean and cut peppers into thin strips.
Peel, slice and cut onion into strips.
Coarsely chop tomatoes.
Cut sausage links into 1/2-inch slices.
Cook in heavy Dutch oven over medium heat until no longer pink.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients to Dutch oven.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with slotted spoon.

title: orange cream congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Combine cream cheese, sugar and orange juice. Mix thoroughly. Gradually add jello and milk to cream cheese mixture. Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in Cool Whip. Chill until set.

title: orange slice cake and icing
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add 1 cup buttermilk.
Beat well.
Add soda to remaining 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Add to batter.
Combine dry ingredients; add them.
Mix orange slice candy, dates and nuts with 1/2 cup flour.
Add to mixture; beat well.
Line tube pan with well-greased brown paper.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: toffee bars
directions: Grease oblong pan, 13 x 9-inches.
Mix butter, sugars and vanilla thoroughly.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in flour, soda and salt. Mix in walnuts.
Spread in prepared pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top of dough.
Place in preheated oven at 375° for 3 minutes.
Remove and run knife through dough to marbleize.
Return to oven; bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Make up night before and refrigerate.
Makes two loaves of bread.
Use whole wheat bread.

title: zabaglione
directions: Place egg in top of double boiler; add sugar.
Beat with mixer at medium speed until mixture is pale yellow and creamy.
Place water in bottom of double boiler and bring to boil over high heat; reduce to low heat.
Place top of double boiler over simmering water.
Gradually beat 1/4 cup Marsala wine in egg yolk; beat 1 minute.
Gradually add remaining Marsala and white wine.
Continue cooking custard over gently simmering water 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir bottom and sides frequently (do not overcook).
Immediately remove top of double boiler from water and whisk briefly.
Pour into 4 individual serving dishes.
Serve warm or cold with your favorite berries, preserves or cookies.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Slice yellow squash. Boil 10 minutes in water with a little salt added. Drain thoroughly. Mix mayonnaise, salt, pepper, eggs, onion and cheese. Add squash to the mixture and mix gently. Put in casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and drizzle with a little melted butter or oleo.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: low-fat chicken pot pie
directions: Cook 3 chicken breasts in 1 to 2 quarts boiling water for 30 minutes.
In a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, pat cut up chicken, mixed vegetables, cream of chicken soup and 1 cup chicken broth from cooked chicken.
Fix pie crust and add to top.
tags: Healthy Choice cream of chicken soup

title: maui chow fun
directions: Fill 6-quart pot half full with water.
Add oil and bring to a boil.
Add in noodles and boil until soft.
Drain in colander. Dice round onion and cut green onions into 1 1/2-inch lengths. Brown ground pork in oiled 6-quart pot.
After ground pork is brown, add in round onion and cook briefly.

Add in 1/3 portion of noodles, bean sprouts, green onions, salt and pepper and stir. Continue adding in rest of ingredients in 1/3 portions and stir. Cook until desired consistency is reached (usually very shortly after adding and stirring in last batch of ingredients).

title: maple peanut yummies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Cream together shortening and peanut butter.
Gradually add brown sugar, creaming well.
Add maple syrup and egg yolk; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually.
Mix thoroughly.
If desired, chill for easier handling.

title: roast beef (philippine style)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pot, then marinate beef in mixture. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add a cup of water and continue to simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours more or until meat is tender. Taste and correct seasoning, if needed.
Slice crosswise against fibers when serving.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly. Chill.
Stir before serving.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Cut up chicken and trim off fat.
Leave on skin.
Wash and season to taste.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350°
until begins to brown which will be 45 minutes, then put pats of butter on each piece.
Continue to bake until it is brown and the skin is crisp.
Use the drippings for gravy.

title: rice pudding
directions: Makes a large bowl of rice pudding.
Enough to feed a large group, but the recipe can be cut in half.

title: chicken ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop bell pepper, broccoli, water chestnuts and onion.
In bowl, flake chicken.
Add vegetables, cheese and soup.
Mix well.
To assemble and bake ring, unroll crescent dough, separate into 16 triangles.
Arrange in a circles on a pizza pan or cookie sheet with wide ends of triangles over lapping in the center and points towards the outside (should be a 5-inch diameter opening in center of pan).
Scoop chicken mixture evenly onto widest end of each triangle.
Bring points of triangles up over filling and tuck under wide ends of dough at center of ring (filling will not be completely covered).
Bake 25-30 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Cut into 8 servings.

title: tennessee pork ribs (light) sauce
directions: Add all ingredients together and simmer until blended.

title: snow ghost chocolate pie
directions: Add first 5 ingredients.
Bring slowly to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Measure the margarine or butter and sugar into large mixing bowl; beat until well blended. Stir in Rice Krispies cereal, chocolate morsels and raisins.

title: confectionery icing
directions: Mix the sugar, salt and vanilla with enough milk to a spreading consistency.

title: beef stroganoff(reduced fat)
directions: In large skillet, saute beef round in vegetable oil, about 4 minutes.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Saute 3 minutes more.
Boil water and cook noodles.
Combine ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, thyme, green pepper, mustard, milk, cooking sherry and beef broth. Add to beef.
Cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over noodles.

title: scotch cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients as for pie crust.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread about 2/3 of dough into baking sheet (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch), bringing dough up sides of pan. Fill with canned pie filling (any flavor).
Use remaining dough to make lattice top.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned.

title: country fried steak
directions: Pound steak with mallet; cut into serving size pieces.
Put into eggs, coating both sides with 1/2 cup flour.
Brown in oil; set aside.
Cook onions until tender.
Remove onions and set aside. Return steak and add 1/2 to 1 cup of water.
Simmer for 1 hour. Remove steak; add 1/4 cup flour to pan drippings, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and cook until smooth and thick. Add steak and onions and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican strata
directions: Cut centers out of bread.
Set centers aside.
Place remaining bread pieces in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer sausage, cheeses and zucchini.
Beat eggs, add milk, tomato sauce, salsa and salt.
Pour over layers.
Place cut out pieces of bread on top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 55 minutes at 325°, uncovered.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 12.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the chips in double boiler and spread on top. Refrigerate.
Take out 1 hour before cutting.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Add brown meat with onions, rice, soup and milk.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cover with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake until brown.

title: seafood chowder base
directions: *Two Swiss Knorr fish bouillon cubes can be substituted for salt, basil, parsley, thyme and pepper.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butter and oil until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until browned.

title: fresh apricot jam
directions: Cook apricots and sugar in a heavy pan over medium heat with enough water to cover until apricots are tender.
Stir often last 15 minutes of cooking until they are consistency of jam.
More or less sugar may be added.
More water may also be needed to keep fruit from sticking until done.
Store in refrigerator.

title: what's in it bread
directions: Soften yeast in 1 cup warm water 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients except regular flour well.
Add unbleached flour; place dough on floured board and knead, adding 1 to 2 cups more flour.
Put dough in greased bowl and let rise about 2 hours. Punch down, form 2 loaves, place in pans and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mississippi corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
This is one of our favorites.

title: party punch
directions: In a large container mix lemon juice, Kool Aid, pineapple juice, ginger ale, sugar and water. Pour this mixture over sherbet in punch bowl.

title: stir-fry vegies
directions: Slice squash, zucchini and onions.
Add salad dressing.
Cook in a frypan on medium-low until tender.

title: icing for orange slice cake
directions: Let orange juice thaw.
Add brown sugar.
Let stand while cake bakes.
Pour on cake while hot.
Let cake cool in pan before removing.

title: fay's green peppers
directions: Place peppers in a saucepan.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Remove stems and seeds.
Trim bottom of each pepper to allow them to stand upright.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook onion, garlic, parsley or celery 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add bread crumbs, squeezed dry.
Heat well.
Add cut shrimp, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Remove from heat and add egg.
Season to taste.
Fill pepper cups.
Set in pan containing 1/4-inch boiling water.
Dot with butter.
Bake until brown, adding more water if necessary.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove from broth and dice.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until done.
In last ten minutes of cooking add diced chicken back to broth and vegetables.

title: california casserole
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli, cauliflower and carrots in a dish. Mix Cheez Whiz and cream of celery soup.
Pour over vegetables. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Top with fried onions and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: bacon and cheese muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease muffin pan.
Place in oven to heat.
Mix all ingredients.
Blend well.
Spoon batter into pan, filling cups 2/3 full.
Bake 12 minutes or until brown.

title: spanish creme icing
directions: Mix pecans, pineapple and pudding together.
Stir in Cool Whip.

title: vegetable-cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan bring water, bouillon, onion, celery, carrot and broccoli to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Pour into an 8-inch pan and refrigerate until thick.
After mixture thickens, stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours until molded.
Cut and serve immediately.
Keep salad refrigerated.

title: honey mustard tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all your ingredients.
Be sure to mix thoroughly.
Coat tenderloin with mixture.
Roast at 375° until meat thermometer registers 160°.
Slice thinly to serve. Serves 4.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and drain beef and onion. Brown, drain and crumble bacon with meat and next 5 ingredients.
Drain all beans and add to meat mixture.
Mix well and pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pork strips with szechwan sauce
directions: Mix pork, 1/2 teaspoon garlic, 2 tablespoons soy sauce, egg, cornstarch and sherry in bowl; set aside.
Mix remaining 2 tablespoons soy sauce and vinegar; set aside.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt together.
Let stand for 2 hours, then drain.
Boil vinegar, sugar and celery seed together, then pour over cucumbers and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: plum cake or spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding eggs last and one at a time.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: good pound cake
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, sprinkle sugar on top of cake while hot.
Wrap in aluminum foil while hot.
Let stay until cake cools.

title: fresh peach refrigerator cake
directions: Break cake into small pieces into 9-inch pan.
Prepare pudding according to directions on box, using 1 cup milk and 1 cup sour cream.
Pour pudding over cake and mix.
Refrigerate several hours.
When ready to serve, cut cake and spoon fresh peaches over top.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: beefy mac
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Mix all other ingredients together. Add to macaroni.
Cook on top for 15 to 20 minutes or in oven in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potluck bread pudding
directions: Mix well together first 4 ingredients.
Blend in pieces of bread and put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, until set.
Makes 24 servings.

title: punch
directions: Boil water and sugar about 3 minutes. In blender, mix bananas, orange juice, lemonade and pineapple juice. Mix with cooled water and sugar mixture. Freeze in mold or 1/2 gallon container. When ready to use, add 2 (2 liter) ginger ale.

title: frontier beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook onions and sausage in skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until sausage is no longer pink.
Drain sausage.
Mix sausage mixture and remaining ingredients in an ungreased 2-quart dish.
Bake, uncovered, about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: halibut au gratin
directions: Flour and season halibut; brown in oil.
Place in a single layer in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with green onions. Combine the sour cream and Parmesan cheese; spread over fish and onions.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce(serves 1)
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Let stand before serving, about 20 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix in heavy boiler and cook at medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Put a layer of vanilla wafers in baking dish and a layer of sliced bananas. Then another layer of wafers and bananas (approximately 25 wafers and 3 bananas). Then pour thickened pudding over wafers and bananas and serve. You may top with meringue and brown, if you wish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients and bake casserole at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
The last 5 minutes in the oven, sprinkle Durkee French fried onions on top.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: chili rellenos
directions: Layer the chiles in a lightly greased casserole dish.
Mix the cheeses and layer over the chilies.
Add another layer of chiles and cheese.
Beat the eggs and sour cream until well mixed.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: thick barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for about 45 minutes, or until the sauce is very thick.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 2 cups.

title: grandma's apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix apples, flour, sugar and cinnamon. Stir gently.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Dab with butter and pour milk over filling.
Roll top crust same as bottom and lift onto filled pie or decorate with lattice top.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Filling for 1 pie.

title: cabbage noodle soup
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients until bacon is crisp in large pot. Add this to chopped cabbage; continue to cook until limp.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Add pasta and simmer, slowly, until pasta is done.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil hen until tender; take chicken out and debone.
Using broth as water, cook rice as directed on box.
Mix chicken with rice.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Stir and serve.

title: philly pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese, margarine and vanilla. Add eggs and mix
until blended at low speed. Stir in flour and baking powder.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pan. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crab quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix the first 7 ingredients well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and then lower oven temperature to 325° for 40 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Cool for 30 minutes and serve warm.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Lightly grease 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread mustard on one side of each piece of bread.
Cut up bread.
Scatter over bottom of pan. Crumble corned beef over bread.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into thin strips.
In large skillet, heat shortening and brown meat, turning often.
Stir in onion soup mix and 2 cups water.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add peppers.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until meat is tender.
Blend cornstarch with 1/2 cup water.
Stir into skillet.
Cook, while stirring, until thickened. Stir in soy sauce and white pepper.
Serve with rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: flama kuchen(plum cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pit and quarter plums.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Set aside.
In another bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside. Cream the melted butter and sugar. Add eggs, vanilla and milk. Add dry ingredients.
Mix to combine. Don't overmix. Dough is thick.
Place evenly in floured cake pan.
Lay plums in even rows on top of dough. Bake 45 minutes until cake springs back.
Cool and serve.

title: cheese boat
directions: Combine sharp cheese, cream cheese and corned beef in bowl. Mix well.
Add tomato, onions, chili peppers, Tabasco and chili powder.
Mix well.
Cut top off of bread; carve middle out.
Put mixture inside loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cream of broccoli
directions: Add chopped broccoli and onions to boiling water.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add all seasonings and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add 1 pint half and half and butter.
Mix flour and water.
Cook until consistency of thick cream.
Very good.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until its color turns brown, but not done. Drain off all fat. Mix Bisquick, sausage and cheese. Form into 1-inch balls. Bake on cookie sheet in 350° oven until done.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into tart pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Crumble and slightly brown sausage.
Drain off grease; cool. In mixing bowl beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard.
Add cubed bread and stir.
Add cheese and sausage and put in glass baking dish 9 x 13-inch and place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Set out a few minutes after baking, cut and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: taco salad
directions: In frying pan, brown hamburger, onion and taco mix.
Combine all ingredients in pot; simmer until very hot.
Put cheese cubes in each serving bowl.
Pour in hot soup and put crushed corn chips on top.

title: moravian sugar cake
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1/2 tsp. sugar in warm water; let stand 5 minutes. Combine potatoes, 1 c. sugar, shortening, 1/4 c. butter and salt in a large mixing bowl; mix until shortening and butter melt. Stir in yeast mixture. Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, about 1 1/2 hours or until spongy. Stir in eggs and enough flour to make a soft dough that leaves sides of bowl. Shape dough into a ball; place in a well greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, about 2 hours or until doubled in bulk. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface, and knead 5 minutes or until smooth and elastic. Divide dough in half; pat evenly into two greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pans. Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts, about 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk. Press slices of butter into dough at about 1/2 inch intervals in rows. Top each slice of butter with about 1 tsp. brown sugar. Sprinkle cinnamon over entire surface. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cut into 2-inch squares and serve warm.

title: party chicken
directions: Place chipped beef on bottom of baking dish.
Wrap chicken breasts in bacon slice.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except noodles.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Serve over Chinese noodles.

title: quiche
directions: Use 10-inch round baking dish 2 inches deep.
Butter baking dish.
Cut French bread into cubes.
Press down in pan.
(Bread should cover the bottom of pan one-inch deep.)
Over the bread sprinkle cubed ham.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese or a mixture of cheese.
Add the eggs beaten well mixed with milk, salt and pepper. Let stand 30 to 60 minutes or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake for 45 minutes or 1 hour at 350°.

title: becky's brew
directions: To boiling water add the tea bags.
Let steep for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
While still warm, in a gallon container, add sugar, pineapple juice, orange juice and almond extract.
Stir.
Add enough cold water to make a gallon of the drink.
Let it get ice cold before serving.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring water and margarine to boil. Remove from heat. Add flour and stir until mixture forms a ball. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each egg. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Let cool.

title: boiled custard(no eggs)
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Beat with mixer for 1 or 2 minutes.
After this sets awhile, it may be too thick.
If so, add more milk until you have the consistency you desire.
More flavoring may be added, if desired.

title: apricot-cream cheese delite
directions: Place
jello, pineapple and juice in saucepan and bring to boil.
Add sugar, baby food and cream cheese.
Heat slowly until cheese melts.
Cool completely, then chill in refrigerator.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 2/3 cup chopped nuts. Serve chilled.

title: salmon cake with lemon-herb mayonnaise
directions: Combine ingredients in small bowl, blend well.

title: orange pecan muffins
directions: Oven at 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture.
Stir in milk, orange rind and pecans.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: delicious potato doughnuts
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes, sugar, buttermilk and eggs. Stir in butter, baking soda, baking powder, nutmeg, salt and enough of the flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface; pat out to 3/4 inch thickness.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch floured doughnut cutter.
In an electric skillet, heat 1 inch of oil to 350°.
Fry the doughnuts for 2 minutes per side or until browned.
Place on paper towels.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: joanne's toffee bars
directions: Place graham crackers in single layer on bottom of greased jelly roll pan.
Cook butter and brown sugar for 2 minutes and pour over graham crackers.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cut while still warm.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Combine asparagus, broth, 1/2 teaspoon thyme, bay leaf and garlic in large saucepan over medium heat; bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes. Discard bay leaf. Place asparagus mix in blender. Process until smooth. Place flour in pan. Gradually add the milk. Whisk

and stir until blended. Add asparagus mixture and ground nutmeg. Stir to combine. Bring to boil. Reduce; simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove and stir in 1/4 teaspoon thyme, butter, salt and lemon rind. Enjoy!

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Pour pineapple and its juice into saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O until dissolved. Cool. Mix in coconut and buttermilk. Add pecans, if desired. Fold in whipped topping. Pour in Bundt pan or ring mold that has been sprayed lightly with cooking spray. Refrigerate until congealed.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until lemony.
Add cheese, lemon peel and vanilla.
Mix well, according to package and pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Carefully spoon cheese mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until done (test with toothpick).
Cool on rack 1 hour.
Invert on plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: grandma's pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Roll out packaged pie crust and crimp a high edge of dough on pan.
Beat eggs, set aside; add spices & sugar to pumpkin mixture whisk together to blend.
Add in eggs, blend, stir in condensed milk just until blended.

Put pie crust on cookie sheet or oven rack & then pour mixture into crust. Gently push in rack after filling crust to prevent run over (which causes crust to burn). Bake fifteen minutes at 425 degrees in glass or 400 degrees in metal pan, then turn down to 375 degrees and bake 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
If you use a metal pan set oven to 425 to preheat & then put cookie sheet under pan.
Bakes best in glass or ironstone pie plates. Garnish with fresh whipped cream.

title: bourbon punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; chill.
To serve, stir in lemon-lime beverage and club soda; pour mixture over crushed ice. Yields about 3 quarts.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble and drain.
Prepare pie shell.
Mix together cheese and sausage.
Sprinkle in shell. Lightly beat eggs in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour in shell.

title: mai tai steak
directions: In a shallow pan, blend instant meat marinade with pineapple juice, rum and ginger.
Place steak in marinade and pierce both sides all over deeply with kitchen fork.
Marinate and turn occasionally for several hours.
Broil about 5 to 6 minutes on each side for medium doneness.
Carve thin diagonal slices and serve.
Serves 4.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Combine all ingredients except powdered sugar.
Mix until blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into powdered sugar and roll until coated.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove immediately and cool on wire rack.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Mix together and pour
into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set 6 hours or overnight
in
fridge.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with 3 cups grated cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve with fruit.

title: chicken choke soup(chicken artichoke)
directions: Saute together the first 5 ingredients until vegetables begin to sweat, then add flour.
Stir to make roux.
Add chicken stock, artichoke hearts with juice, water, chicken squares, cream, pepper and garlic powder.
Increase heat and cook for 30 minutes, then reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pull from heat and let set 15 minutes before serving.
Garnish with a dollop of sour cream.

title: pink fluff
directions: Mix all together (jello dry).
Drain fruit first. Refrigerate.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in melted butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.
In a small mixer bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold egg whites into lemon batter.
Turn into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Place in larger pan on oven rack.
Pour hot water into larger pan to a depth of 1 inch.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes, or until top is golden and springs back when touched.
Serve warm or chilled in individual dessert dishes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Add 2 cups hot water to jello; drain pineapple, bananas and strawberries.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour half in casserole dish and chill; spread sour cream and add top.
Delicious!

title: bun in foil
directions: Mix bacon, dried beef, chili sauce and relish together. Spread on bun.
Top with a slice of cheese and wrap buns individually in foil.
Put in oven for about 10 minutes, until heated.

title: barbecued lima beans
directions: "Blessed is the man be he ever so humble, whose stomach can take all he's given and not grumble."

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix dough and butter and special sugar for 1 day.
Then add the rest of the ingredients and mix for another day.
Put scoops about 1 tablespoon (big) on a pan, bake it in a 20° oven for 15 hours.

title: yellow rose of texas chili
directions: Cook meat with onions until browned.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, chilies (do not drain juices) and beans.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder to taste!
Simmer at least 1 hour, the longer the better.

title: meatball madness
directions: Spread tomato sauce on crust of your choice. Top with meatball slices. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Serves 2.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with Doritos or large Fritos.
Add a few drops Tabasco sauce (if desired) or chopped green chilies.
Serves 4.

title: sunbonnet casserole
directions: Cook the noodles in boiling salted water until tender (about 5 minutes).
Drain and rinse.
While the noodles are cooking, combine the cream of celery soup and milk; mix well.
Add the eggs, green pepper, onion and pimiento.
Fold into the noodles. Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole or 4 individual casseroles. Sprinkle with the bread crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until lightly browned (about 20 minutes).
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Use galvanized or crock container.
Soak whole cucumbers in salt water that will float an egg for 14 days.
Drain and slice cucumbers thin.
Add box of alum to water to cover sliced cucumbers (let stand overnight).
Drain and pour 1 gallon of vinegar over cucumbers.
Let stand at least 6 hours.
Drain off vinegar (save for another batch).
Put layer of cucumbers in crock or churn.
Add sugar and pickling spices.
Keep layering until all are covered with sugar and spices.
These can be eaten after 5 days.
Better if they stand longer.

title: bavarian cream pudding
directions: Soften the gelatin in water a few minutes. Beat yolks and sugar until very light. Add the softened gelatin. Cook in double boiler until the mixture coats the spoon, stirring constantly. Let cool. Add vanilla and fold in the whipped cream. Turn into a mold lined with ladyfingers.
Let stand several hours to chill. Serve with fresh fruit, caramel or chocolate sauce.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix together
boiling
water,
gelatin,
cold water and sugar. Mix pineapple, coconut, nuts, vanilla and lemon juice. Whip 3 packages
of
Dream
Whip.
Take large angel food cake, pull apart in chunks.
Place
in
large tube cake pan and pour the other ingredients over cake (except Dream Whip).
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Just before serving, ice cake with Dream Whip.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Peel and chop apples.
Chop tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a rapid boil, then simmer until thick.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Drain spinach.
Melt oleo and blend with flour.
Mix all other ingredients with flour mixture and add to eggs, a little at a time.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a greased pan.

title: split pea soup
directions: Rinse
split
peas
and
add to the gallon of water the salt, the
pepper,
the
onions
and the beef base.
Let boil until peas are
done.
Mix the flour and the cooking oil to a smooth texture and
add
gradually
to
the soup mixture until there is a smooth texture, not too thick.
Let cook over a low fire for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: tang tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in airtight container.
To serve, add 2 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water.
Stir well.

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: Note:
If using cake mix with pudding in mix, omit instant pudding mix.
Use 3 eggs instead of 4, 1/3 cup of oil instead of 1/2 cup.

title: honey peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Butter an 8-cup casserole.
Put peaches in prepared casserole dish.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Combine lemon juice and honey and pour over peaches.
Blend flour, oats, cinnamon and butter until crumbly.
Spread over peaches.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until peaches are tender and top is slightly brown.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding well beaten eggs lastly. Bake at 425° in greased corn bread pan until done, about 30 minutes.

title: ma casey's combination crawfish pasta
directions: Melt butter; saute vegetables.
Add flour and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add crawfish, half and half and cheeses, being careful not to let mixture stick to bottom.
(It will burn easily.)
Add seasoning to taste.
Simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.
Serve on cooked pasta.

title: bavarian apple strudel
directions: Sift the flour and salt into a bowl.
Stir in the mixed oil, egg and water.
Knead to a dough and continue kneading for about 10 minutes.
Cover and leave in a warm place for 30 minutes.
Peel and core the apples.
Slice thinly and sprinkle with lemon juice. Roll out the dough on a floured cloth, then stretch it until very thin.
Brush with the melted butter, then with the sour cream. Top with apple slices, raisins and sugar.
Roll up the strudel, using the cloth to lift it.
Cut into portions to fit one or 2 greased baking sheets.
Brush with milk and bake in a hot oven at 450°
for 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown.
Brush with milk 3 to 4 times during baking.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken pie
directions: Have fryer boiled and cooled.
Remove meat from bones and cut up into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
(Spray dish with Pam.)
Cut boiled eggs over meat.
Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Combine celery soup and broth.
Bring to a boil to dissolve lumps by stirring. Pour over the eggs and meat.
Mix milk and flour into a bowl until most of lumps are gone.
Spoon over the top of mixture.
Dot with butter.
Cook in 350° oven about 45 minutes to an hour.
Be sure the top of pie is slightly brown.

title: the cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: sears' honeycomb candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and vinegar in heavy kettle. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Using candy thermometer, cook to 300°. When candy reaches 300°, turn off heat immediately and quickly stir in baking soda.
Pour into lightly greased 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Cool 4 hours. Break or cut into desired pieces.
Dip pieces into melted chocolate and refrigerate until chocolate is set.

title: cloud cake
directions: Will also need a shallow pan, approximately 17 1/2 x 11-inches.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie crusts.
Put one 9-inch pie crust in bottom of a 9-inch pie plate.
Mix all other ingredients and pour into crust.
Place the other 9-inch pie crust on top. Crimp edges to seal. Cut slits in pie crust .
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: whole wheat banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and honey together.

Add eggs; mix well. Stir in bananas. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with hot water. Mix until smooth. Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool on wire rack for 1/2 hour before slicing. Freezes well.

title: pecan ditty
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar and heat until stiff.
Roll crackers fine and fold into egg whites and add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in buttered pie pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Beat whipped cream.
Add preserves. Place in cooled shell.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Whip condensed milk until fluffy.
Add lemonade and whip until fluffy.
Beat in Cool Whip until light and fluffy.
Pour in graham cracker crust. Chill for 3 hours.

title: play dough
directions: Mix together in saucepan the flour, salt and cream of tartar. Stir in the water, oil and food coloring.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until ball forms.
Remove from heat; knead as soon as possible when you are able to handle mixture. Put in airtight plastic container to keep moist.

title: creamy coconut pie
directions: Beat cream cheese in a mixing bowl until soft; beat in sugar. Gradually add milk and beat until smooth.
Fold in coconut and Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm (about 4 hours). Toast coconut to garnish.
Let thaw to serve.
Keep leftovers in freezer.

title: diabetic cornbread
directions: Mix all together and pour in skillet. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: egg salad
directions: Dice eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Serve on crisp greens or use for stuffing mushrooms, small tomatoes or any other vegetable which lends itself to stuffing.
May be used as sandwich spread.
Serves 6.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix until smooth, then pour half in a greased tube pan.
Put a layer of apple slices on the batter, then sprinkle sugar and cinnamon to suit your taste. Cover with the rest of the batter.
Arrange remaining apple slices on top and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until done, about 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: mom's rice pudding
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Combine and beat eggs, Milnot, water, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Put rice in baking dish; add raisins and egg mixture.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° in a pan of water for about 55 minutes.

title: jennie's breakfast casserole
directions: Spray microwave-proof casserole dish with Pam.
Spread frozen hash browns in casserole.
Microwave on High 10 minutes (may vary with different microwaves).
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over potatoes.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes, giving dish a quarter turn after 4 to 5 minutes.
Cook until egg mixture in center of casserole has set. Top with crumbled sausage and shredded cheese.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and cut in wedges.

title: ms. lindsey's cole slaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pepper.
Blend well and pour over vegetables.
Stir until vegetables are nicely coated.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie crust. In at least an 8-cup microwavable glass bowl, add sugar and cornstarch. Whisk together until blended. Add Sprite and whisk until well blended. Place in microwave and cook as follows:
4:44, stir with whisk; 3:33, stir with whisk; 2:22, stir with whisk; 1:11, stir with whisk. Add Jell-O and let cool. Put strawberries in baked pie crust. Pour mixture over strawberries.

title: enchiladas(makes 24 enchiladas)
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add beans, chili peppers and chili. Cook for about 1 hour.
Tortillas must be dipped in remainder of sauce, then fill and roll.
Cover with grated cheese.

title: clam chowder
directions: Pour clams with juice over potatoes and celery; add water just to cover vegetables.
Boil until tender.
Drain, except for very small amount (liquid depends on how thick you want chowder).

title: chili cheese casserole
directions: Layer chilies, Cheddar, chilies and Cheddar in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, Worcestershire sauce and corn meal.
Pour over cheese and chilies and bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Take out of oven and put 1/2 of Monterey Jack cheese, tomato sauce and other 1/2 of Jack cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes more. Good with hamburgers, steaks and etc.

title: easy brownies
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar and eggs.
Beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
These are a fudge brownie.

title: pizza dough
directions: Combine 1/4 cup warm water, yeast and 1/2 teaspoon sugar in a cup; let it bubble to top.

title: pennsylvania dutch red beet eggs
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, except onion and eggs.
Slice onion thinly and separate into rings.
Pour beet mixture into a deep bowl.
Remove bay leaf and cloves.
Add onion; stir.
Add eggs, making sure they are submerged.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
(The longer the eggs stay in the pickle, the deeper color they will develop.)

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Spread raisins and nuts in bottom of pan. Place frozen rolls in pan.
Put pudding mix and brown sugar together and sprinkle on top.
Cover with foil and let rise overnight.
In the morning, uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert on plate.

title: corkscrew casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in Pam-coated 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and cover with cheese slices.
Return to oven until cheese melts. Serves 6.

title: slushies drink mix
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Pour mixture into water.
Stir thoroughly.
Put container in freezer to form "slushy."

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl; mix by hand.
Bake in a greased and floured angel cake pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan 1 hour.
When cool, frost with cream cheese icing.

title: coconut pie
directions: Using large bowl, beat eggs until mixed well.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Melt margarine.
Add to other mixture.
Add buttermilk and coconut.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into shells.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until brown.

title: bubble-up pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Quarter biscuits. Stir in 1 cup of sauce and 2 cups of cheese. Press garlic clove and add to mixture. Add desired optional ingredients and mix. Spread mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish. Pour remaining sauce and cheese over top. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until sides are golden brown. Yield:
12 servings.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Stir and bring to boil.
Boil for 3 minutes and place in hot jars and seal.

title: caponata
directions: Wash and dice eggplant.
Salt and layer for 1 hour.
Rinse. (Takes away bitterness.)
Fry onion; add peeled, chopped tomatoes, diced celery, pitted olives and capers.
As soon as tomatoes are cooked, remove from heat.
Rinse and dry eggplant.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Put into tomato mixture.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Stir and cook five minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: waldorf astoria stew
directions: Mix together and place in large casserole.
Bake at 250° for 8 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line bowl with cookies.
Let Cool Whip set out to soften. Make pudding according to directions.
Add a little extra milk. Stir slowly.
Add extracts.
Add Cool Whip as desired.
Cut up bananas. Add, stirring slowly. Top with cookie crumbs. Delicious.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine egg, salt and buttermilk.
Blend well and stir in flour, meal and sugar.
Mix well.
Bake at 400°
until brown.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and salt together.
Let stand 1 hour. Drain well, but don't rinse.
Mix white sugar, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and powdered alum together.
Boil all together for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers and refrigerate.

title: pickles
directions: Drain all juice off the pickles.
Add sugar. Replace lid to jar. Set aside for 2 days and then they are ready to eat and enjoy.

title: milk shakes
directions: Place ice cream and milk into blender.
Mix until smooth. Enjoy!

title: strawberry-banana jello salad
directions: Make the jello with 2 cups of boiling water.
Do not add cold water!
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl; add the jello.
Pour into a mold or an 8 x 8-inch baking dish or a bowl.
Chill until set.
Enjoy!

title: pepper sauce
directions: You will need any size jars with lids.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Drain pineapple and apricots, reserving syrups.
Place dried fruit in large saucepan; add syrups, cinnamon sticks, cloves and bourbon.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add pineapple, apricots, cherries and grapes, then simmer five more minutes.
Serve warm as accompaniment to ham or poultry.
Serves 12; any leftovers will be delicious served hot or cold over vanilla ice cream.

title: party fruit dip
directions: Mix rum flavoring, sweetener and cream cheese together until soft.
Then add lite Cool Whip.

title: coke cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour and sugar together; stir in marshmallows and set aside.
Bring to a boil, shortening, oleo, cocoa and Coke.
Remove from heat and pour over dry ingredients. Stir in buttermilk, baking soda and eggs.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. Note:
You do not beat the mixture.
Cool about 30 minutes before icing cake.

title: jeanne's spinach salad
directions: Add grated carrot for color or any veggie you like.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In an electric fry pan, place first 3 ingredients. Cook slowly until golden brown, then add the remaining ingredients. Cover and let cook 30 minutes on medium heat until liquid is absorbed.

title: peanut butter critters
directions: Bring sugar and Karo syrup to a boil, but do not let boil. Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
When peanut butter is dissolved, add Corn Flakes.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: banana macadamia nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine first 8 ingredients.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes).
Add bananas and orange juice.
Continue beating until well mixed (1 minute).
By hand, stir in coconut and nuts.
(Batter will be thick.)

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except cinnamon in a casserole dish (1 1/2-quart size for standard serving).
Mix thoroughly.
Place casserole in a pan filled with 1 inch deep hot water.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes (or until knife inserted halfway comes out clean).
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serve warm or cold.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix up diced bread, crouton crumbs and cornbread a day ahead. Cook celery, onion and chicken broth until celery and onion are tender.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Beat all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: delicious fruit punch
directions: Mix water and sugar and bring to a boil.
Stir in pineapple juice, lemon juice and orange juice.
Mash banana and add to juices.
Put in freezer and freeze.
When ready to serve, pour ginger ale over frozen mixture.
Take out 2 hours before serving.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook beans about 5 to 8 minutes; drain.
Add to other ingredients.
Put Ritz crackers (crushed) on top.
Bake.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° in greased, floured tube pan.
Makes a very moist cake.

title: tuna casserole with noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple and cherry filling in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Stir.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling.
Drizzle 1 stick melted oleo over dry mix.
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 5 can soup
directions: Mix together in pot.
Heat until hot.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: holiday herb cheese spread
directions: Beat together cream cheese and butter until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients except red bell pepper; beat well.
Place a piece of plastic wrap on a small cookie sheet.
Spoon cheese mixture onto plastic wrap to form a log about 3-inches thick and 12-inches long.
Fold up plastic wrap over cheese to encase. Refrigerate until cheese is firm, about 4 hours or overnight.

title: angel biscuits (buttermilk)
directions: These are yeast biscuits and the dough can be kept in the refrigerator for several days so the family can have fresh baked bread for several nights.

title: black bottoms
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until well blended.
Fill lined muffin cup 1/3 full.

title: herbed tomato soup
directions: In 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan, saute celery and onion.
Mix in garlic, bouillon cubes, water, herbs and pepper.
Stir until cubes dissolve.
Simmer, uncovered, until vegetables are just tender, about 8 minutes.
Mix in tomatoes, coarsely chopped, with liquid and tomato paste.
Cook gently about 10 more minutes.
Good served with grilled cheese or egg salad sandwich.

title: 100 cookies
directions: Mix in order given and chill 1 hour. Flatten a bit with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
You may add chocolate chips, raisins, fruit cake mix, candied cherries, whatever.

title: 4-h layer cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening and vanilla.
Add sugar and eggs.
Add milk and dry ingredients, one-third of each at a time.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: party trifle
directions: Prepare brownies as directed; add 1/2 cup of the nuts to batter before baking.
Cool in pan.
Cut into 1/2 inch squares.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Gently stir in 4 cups of the whipped topping.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Layer 1/2 of the brownies, strawberries, chopped candy bars, remaining 1 cup nuts and pudding mixture in 5-quart serving bowl.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining whipped topping.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Garnish as desired.

title: fudgy mint cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate with 1/2 cup margarine. In bowl, combine chocolate mixture with sugar, 3 eggs, vanilla and flour.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 12 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix and form into ball.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cut carrots and cook in salted water until crisp-tender. Drain, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Mix onion, horseradish, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and carrot liquid.
Combine with carrots in buttered casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs with melted margarine and spread over carrots.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients together.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Makes 6 servings.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Very lightly grease a 10 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Cut dried beef in 1/2-inch strips; cover bottom of the casserole dish.
Lay chicken on top of dried beef.
In a mixing bowl, combine sour cream and cream of mushroom soup; pour over chicken.
Cover with tinfoil; bake for 2 hours at 200°. Great served over rice!!!
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: white chili
directions: Cook 1 pound chicken breasts, diced, in 2 teaspoons olive oil. Set aside.
Saute until tender onion and garlic.
Stir in tomatillas, tomatoes, chicken broth, green chilies, oregano, cumin and coriander.
Bring this to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Return chicken to pot.
Add white kidney beans and lime juice.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: slush(summer drink)
directions: Measure sugar and water into saucepan.
Heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a boiling point, let boil for one minute.
Refrigerate until cold.
Mix chilled mixture with pineapple juice, orange juice, and lemon concentrate and bananas. Pour into 5 (1-quart) containers.
Cover and freeze.
At serving time, half fill tall glass with soda of your choice.
Spoon frozen mixture to fill.
Serve with a straw and a spoon.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Mix together cream cheese, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Add crabmeat and onion.
Turn into 8-inch pie plate.
Top with almonds, placed in a circle around the outer edge.

title: heath candy bar cake
directions: In saucepan, combine water, oil, margarine and cocoa. Bring to a full boil, stir and remove from heat. Let cool.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a nine-inch spring-form pan.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast, 1 teaspoon salt in 2 cups lukewarm water.
Add enough flour to make sponge and let rise in warm place 2 hours. Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add 2 cups flour alternating with 1 cup cold water.
Combine with sponge mixture.
Mix well.
Knead in enough flour to make consistency of bread dough.
Let rise twice, kneading down each time.
Make into cloverleaf rolls.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Keep dough in refrigerator. Knead down each day.
Use as desired.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen rolls.

title: anna's biscuits
directions: Mix creamer and flour; cut in Crisco. Add water and mix until moistened. Pinch off dough and shape; place on a greased pan and bake at 450° until brown.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook sausage.
Add tomato paste and water.
Layer biscuits in pan.
Top with tomato mixture (sprinkle garlic and oregano on top of biscuits first).
Add any toppings you desire.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until done.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Add onion and simmer until clear.
Add broccoli and stir thoroughly. Add soup. Stir and simmer.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in rice and bake in a casserole at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sue's chicken
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Cut up chicken and roll in 2 packages of onion soup mix.
Then put in pan and cover in oven with foil (poke holes in foil).
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, then take off cover and put mushrooms over all; cook, uncovered, for 1/2 hour.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend all ingredients, except pineapple.
Pour into prepared pan. Top with crushed pineapple. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Top with your favorite icing, then spread remaining pineapple on top.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Add all ingredients.
Place in an 8-inch greased square pan. Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes, being careful not to overbake.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, milk and salt.
Then roll into balls the size you wish and put in a glass pan.
Set aside.
Mix Worcestershire, vinegar, sugar, water, ketchup and chopped onion.
Pour this over the meatballs and bake uncovered for 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: sweet red pepper soup
directions: Saute onion in olive oil in a large Dutch oven for 5 minutes or until tender.
Add sweet red pepper and broth; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
