Cook broccoli, drain and add soup, onion, rice and cheese.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish. Cook at 350° until bubbly, about 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In large skillet, fry onion in butter. Add broccoli and all other ingredients except crumbs. Stir together until cheese is melted. Pour into 9 x 13 dish. Pour crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry philly pie
directions: Combine the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Mix with strawberries.
Put in pie shell.

title: caesar salad
directions: Wash and dry lettuce.
Tear into bite size pieces and put into large salad bowl.
Add croutons and salad dressing; toss well.
Sprinkle with bacon bits and Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and fry.
Arrange in a baking dish.
Cover with gravy or 1 can mushroom or celery soup, diluted with a little water.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
This may require a little water if zucchini is grated in a vegetable processor.
Batter will be thin.

title: strawberry ice cream pie
directions: Mix together sesame seed, flour, salt, sugar and shortening. Roll out; form in 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned and cool.

title: green tomato and raspberry jam
directions: Bring to a boil the green tomatoes and sugar.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Add raspberry Jell-O; stir well and seal.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients together, make into small balls or roll out with a rolling pin and cut out with cookie cutter one-inch in diameter.
Bake in oven at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough into balls, using a rounded teaspoon.

title: cream cheese pastry cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Mix in flour and salt until a ball forms.
Chill.

title: blueberry whipped cream delight
directions: Mix margarine, flour, sugar and walnut pieces.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir.
Press while hot into a 9-inch pie pan.

title: baked chicken
directions: Layer chicken in bottom of baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Take out of oven.
Pour sweet and sour sauce over baked chicken.
Cut bell peppers in strips and put on top of baked chicken.
Put back in oven for 30 more minutes.

title: banana refresher
directions: Blend all but ice cream until smooth. Add ice cream and blend until smooth.
Makes 4 (6 ounce) servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Add blueberries.
Fill greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1/2 cup water about 5 minutes after bringing to a boil.
Drain and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add cheese to top of broccoli.
Mix Pet milk and mushroom soup together; pour over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes.
Remove and add onions; cook another 10 minutes or until brown.

title: banana raspberry smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; process until smooth.

title: butter mint ice cream
directions: Cook beaten eggs with approximately 1 1/2 cups milk and butter mints.
Cool and combine with other ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer container.
Finish filling with milk.
Process.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Season meat.
Brown in shortening.
Remove meat.
Saute onion. Stir in soup, water and Worcestershire.
Put meat in mixture; simmer for two hours.
Add sour cream before serving over noodles.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Boil all together. Add 1 large can of peaches with juice. Chill.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain 1 can crushed pineapple; put all ingredients together in large bowl except Cool Whip.
Stir thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip and chill for 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: stromboli
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Roll dough to pie crust thickness. In middle of dough put 1/4 of sausage, pepperoni and cheese.
Fold over dough, layer again.
Cut in half, fold over edges.
Place on cookie sheet.
Repeat with other loaf.
Brush top with egg white cut into 1 inch pieces.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serve with warm pizza sauce.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and blend.
Add pecans until well mixed.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press pecan mixture in butter.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes; stir every 10 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the shortening with the sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Make a paste of the cocoa and food coloring.
Add to creamed mixture. Sift flour and salt twice.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour to creamed mixture. Add vanilla.
Put vinegar in deep bowl.
Add soda (it will foam).
When blended, add to creamed cake batter.
Do not beat batter, just blend well. Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans.
Pour batter into pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter rice krispies treats
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large saucepan over low heat, stir together Karo, sugar and peanut butter.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in Rice Krispies. Press into ungreased pan.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: millionaire torte
directions: Bake the cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 12 minutes. Cool.
Slowly blend the milk with the cream cheese and pudding. Pour over cake; let set.
Spread drained crushed pineapple over pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Refrigerate.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon.
Mix all ingredients.
Put bacon on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash and add eggs, soup, salt, pepper, onions and about 10 crumbled crackers.
Stir in cheese.
Pour into casserole.
Top with more crumbled crackers.
Dot with butter. Cook at 350° until set, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: jello salad
directions: Beat cottage cheese with mixer at high speed until curds are smaller.
Add dry jello and mix well.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Add fruit and pecans.
Stir well; refrigerate.

title: rice consomme
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Put pecans, sugar and salt in a large heavy skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring the mixture constantly.
Cook sugar-nut mixture until sugar melts and turns a rich golden color.
Transfer nut mixture to waxed paper and let cool slightly.
Separate nuts.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend all ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef; drain off excess grease.
Add soup, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Heat.
Stir well. Spoon onto buns and serve.

title: avocado mousse
directions: Mash avocado flesh with plenty of lemon juice to prevent discoloration.
Add chopped onion and Worcestershire sauce. Dissolve gelatin in the water over a pan of hot water and add to mixture along with chicken stock.
Leave until the point of setting.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Lastly, fold in the stiffly whipped egg whites.
Turn into a 2 1/2-pint (1 1/2 liter) oiled ring mold and refrigerate.

title: hobo stew
directions: You will need 2 long strips of aluminum foil.

title: peanut butter snackin' bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat the condensed milk, peanut butter, egg, water and vanilla until smooth. Add biscuit mix; mix well.
Stir in chips.
Spread evenly in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store, tightly covered, at room temperature.
Makes 36 bars.

title: fried frogs' legs
directions: Season frog legs with salt and pepper.
Dip in beaten eggs and crumbs.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Fry in hot fat until brown.

title: sky high coconut cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; stir in sugar, cornstarch, salt, butter, vanilla and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boil, about 3 minutes.
Pour in coconut and mix, then put in pastry shell.
Put meringue on top.
Sprinkle some coconut on top of meringue.
Put in oven and brown.
Let cool 5 hours before cutting.

title: football cake
directions: Dissolve soda in boiling water in large bowl; add sugar, shortening, eggs, salt, cocoa, buttermilk, vanilla and flour. Mix with electric mixer at slow speed until all ingredients are moistened. Increase mixer speed until medium and beat for 2 minutes. Bake as a sheet cake in oiled, paper-lined pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until batter springs back when touched lightly in the center. Take out of oven and let cool for 5 to 10 minutes, then turn out on rack to finish cooling.

title: cheese crisps
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter until fluffy.
Slowly mix in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in cheese and cereal.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm or cold.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: chicken delight
directions: Roll legs in butter, then in combined bread, cheese and seasonings.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raspberry whip pie
directions: Use 8 or 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water stirring 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir until gelatin is thick (2 to 3 minutes).
Remove unmelted ice.
Blend in Cool Whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in buttered baking dish.
Pour water over apples and sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Cream the butter, add flour and brown sugar and sugar and blend.
Put mixture on apples.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 40 to 45 minutes or until top is browned.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: 1. Beat pulp, soda, sugar, and shortening until creamy. Add egg and rest of ingredients.
2. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
3. Bake at 375° for 12-15 minutes

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter on one slice of bread; then spread the other slice of bread with jelly.
Place slices of bread together, having the peanut butter and jelly in the middle.
And enjoy.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Mix
lemon juice, Eagle Brand milk and sugar; mix well. Let stand for 1/2 hour.
Add milk and lemon extract.
Freeze.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions; drain. Combine mayonnaise, milk and soup. Add Cheddar cheese, dill weed and tuna. Stir in the cooked noodles and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle top with buttered bread crumbs or cracker crumbs or French fried onions or crushed potato chips. Bake 5 minutes more. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and raisins(chicken la magnificient)
directions: Brown thighs in margarine in a skillet.
Add onions on top. Pour water in, just to cover chicken.
Cover skillet.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add raisins and simmer (covered) for 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serve with mashed potatoes.
Pour gravy over potatoes.
Sweet and savory!

title: homemade irish cream liquor
directions: Put in blender.
Store in refrigerator for a month.
Stir before serving.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Season meat with salt and brown in oil.
Arrange alternately layers of meat, potatoes and onion in 2-quart casserole.
Pour soup over layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(When I make this casserole, I drain meat.
I use enough potatoes and onion to make complete layer of each.
I also use 2 cans mushroom soup, using 1 can on top of first 3 layers and 2nd can over top of casserole.)

title: roly-polies cookie
directions: Cream shortening and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Add flour mixture and blend well.
Chill dough for 2 hours. Grease baking sheets.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon; put in a bowl.
Roll dough into small balls and dip and roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: herb and parmesan crescent strips
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 2 long rectangles. Unroll 1 rectangle onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons cheese, basil and oregano.
Unroll second rectangle; place over cheese and herbs.
Roll with a rolling pin to flatten slightly.
Brush with egg.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cheese.

title: lo-cal italiano string beans
directions: Slowly
simmer
tomato juice with garlic salt, oregano, parsley and
basil
until reduced to half its original volume. Add beans; stir.
Cover;
remove from heat and let stand for 2 minutes before serving.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: *If nuts are omitted, add an additional 1/2 cup chocolate chips.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Put rhubarb and jello on top of marshmallows.
Make yellow or white cake mix according to directions and put on top.
Top with whipped cream when cooled.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples, 5 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside. Sift together flour, baking powder and 2 cups of sugar.
Add nuts. Set aside.
In large bowl, beat for 5 minutes, eggs, oil, orange juice and vanilla.
Stir into flour mixture until well blended. Put into either a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or greased and floured angel food cake pan in the following order:
1/3 batter, 1 layer apple mixture, 1/3 batter, 1 layer apple mixture, 1/3 batter, ending with apple mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: crumb cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Work in margarine as mixing biscuits.
Reserve one cup of mixture.
To the rest add egg and combine with milk.
Beat with electric mixer.
Transfer to shallow pan rubbed with shortening or sprayed with Pam and dusted with flour.
Add cinnamon and brown sugar to reserved one cup of dry mix.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is done.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients by hand until mixed and smooth. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Don't open door until done.
Cool before icing.

title: meatless stuffed peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut peppers in half lengthwise; remove seeds and stems.
Place peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes or until slightly softened.
Drain; set aside.

title: joyce smith's bubble magic
directions: Purchase glycerin from your pharmacist.
Mix all ingredients gently; let stand 24 hours.
(This fluid will make much stronger bubbles than commerical type.)
Take an ample supply of bubble fluid, a jelly roll pan, the latest in bubble wands and one child or grandchild to the park.
Pour fluid into jelly roll pan (dipping horizontally instead of vertically distributes the fluid more evenly).
Do not agitate fluid when dipping - froth does not make good bubbles.
This is an excellent way for single parents or grandparents to meet same of opposite gender - that's the magic!

title: mushroom marinade
directions: Whisk all ingredients except mushrooms in deep bowl until well combined. Add mushrooms. Cover and marinate in refrigerator 4 hours or preferably overnight.

title: memaw's fresh fridge pickles
directions: Scrape cucumbers with a nylon scourer or vegetable brush to remove wax.
Bring sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed to a boil; let cool.
Slice cucumbers, onions and peppers.
When liquid is cool, pour over cuke mixture in a covered glass container or crock.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Put mixture into pint jars with tight-fitting lids.
Store all covered jars in refrigerator.
Makes 5 pints.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Bring half and half to boil.
Add partially thawed potatoes. Cook until liquid is absorbed.
Mix other ingredients except cheese.
Pour into large greased casserole and top with cheese. Bake at 350°
for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all ingredients; will be very thin.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
May be doubled; will fill an enamel turkey roaster.

title: chicken burrito
directions: Boil chicken 1 hour.
Add salt to your taste.
Cool for 25 minutes.
Take chicken off bones.
Cut chicken with food chopper. Place in large skillet.
Add salsa sauce and enchilada sauce. Simmer over low heat for 25 minutes.
Serve over brown rice.

title: salsa dip
directions: Microwave Velveeta cheese and salsa or picante sauce in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl on High for 5 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.

title: no-mess microwave peanut brittle
directions: Spray Baker's Joy on a jelly roll pan.
In a one-quart glass casserole dish or bowl, combine sugar, peanuts, salt and corn syrup.
Microwave on Medium power for 4 minutes.
Remove and stir. Microwave on Medium for an additional five minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to package. Line bottom of greased casserole dish (large size) with broccoli. Then place chicken on top.
Next, sprinkle the shredded cheese on top.
Melt the margarine and combine with the dressing crumbs. Place on top of cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, keeping it covered until the last few minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Chop onion.
Brown
meat with onion.
Drain.
Add corn, Ro-Tel and tomatoes.
Mix corn bread as directed.
Pour batter on top of meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain well.
Mix with other ingredients. Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan.
In bacon fat, fry onion and pepper until soft.
In a large pot, combine lima beans (drained of juice), onion, green pepper, chili sauce and sugar.
Add bacon which has been broken in pieces.
Mix well and bake, uncovered, in a 300° oven.
Stir occasionally.

title: children's bird seed(trail mix)
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and serve as a snack.
Great to take along on trips to the park or zoo.

title: mexican hot wheels
directions: Chop very fine the peppers, black olives and green onions. Add to pimento and cream cheese.
Spread on flour tortilla and roll up.
Chill several hours in refrigerator.
To serve, slice in thin slices.
May be kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: In an oblong cake pan, spread soup on bottom.
Place chicken breasts on top of soup.
Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt.
Place small tablespoon of margarine on chicken.
Spread sour cream over margarine and chicken.
Sprinkle with dried onions.
Bake for 1 hour in oven at 350°.

title: layered salad
directions: In large bowl, layer half of all ingredients.
Sprinkle teaspoon sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper on top. Mix mayonnaise and yogurt well.
Spread 1/2 of dressing on top. Repeat with all other ingredients, ending with dressing.
Spread other cheese pressing on top.
Cover and chill.

title: easy meal baked pork chops
directions: Heat oil; saute chops quickly.
Remove to plate as they brown; add more oil if needed to saute rice, onion and pepper, until rice is golden.
Place chops on top of rice.
Pour tomatoes over chops. Then sprinkle oregano; add vinegar.
Cover tightly.
Cook at 350° in oven or on top of stove until meat and rice are tender.
Check now and then to see if more water is needed.

title: blackeyed peas, tomatoes, bacon
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion.
Add black-eyed peas and tomato wedges.
Cook until almost dry.
Add several slices of crisp bacon, crumbled.

title: hot spiced juice
directions: Heat and serve hot.
Does really well perked in coffeepot with sugar and spices in strainer.

title: party punch
directions: Mix and pour back into gallon jugs until ready to use and refrigerate.
Add ice.
Will fill punch bowl twice.
Very tasty and pretty for fall.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Add shortening, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and egg. Mix together well.
Blend in flour. Chill for 1 hour in refrigerator.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: bonbons
directions: Pour melted butter over chopped pecans.
Mix in powdered sugar, Eagle Brand milk and coconut.
Roll into balls.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: cream of celery soup
directions: Cook celery in stock and water until soft and rub through sieve.
Scald onion in milk; remove onion.
Add milk to stock. Bind with butter and flour cooked together.
Add cream.
Season and reheat.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine the oats and milk; let stand for 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat a nonstick pan over medium low heat. Pour 1/4 cup of batter per pancake onto the skillet.
Cook, turning once, until golden brown on both sides.
Serve with spread.

title: texas brag cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of pan, then spoon in pineapple. Next, spread cake mix; lightly pat down.
Spread coconut and nuts. Pour margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine. Add Crispix to melted chocolate.
Coat good.
Pour 1/2 bag of sugar in bag and shake.
Put in freezer for a few minutes to firm, then add more sugar to finish coating.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients; let stand at room temperature for a few hours or overnight.
Add chicken wings; coat with marinade.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 days, stirring twice a day.
Put on cookie sheets lined with aluminum foil.
Drain marinade and place wings in a single layer.
Cook without turning for 1/2 to 3/4 hour, or until brown, in a 350° oven.
Can be frozen.
Thaw and reheat in a 350° oven for approximately 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb jello jam
directions: Put on low heat.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add 1 (3 ounce) box strawberry Jell-O.
Put in jars.
Seal and freeze.

title: lima beans and bacon
directions: Cover beans with
water
and boil for 20 to 25 minutes. Crumble the bacon and
add to the beans.
Add the salt and the pepper; cook until tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon cheese pineapple cake
directions: On the first 7 ingredients, cream sugar and shortening on high speed.
Add one egg white at a time beating for one minute after each addition.
Turn mixer on low, add vanilla, cake flour with baking powder and milk alternately mixing well.
Bake at 350° 20 minutes.
This makes 3 layers.
Next, mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, 3/4 cup butter, lemon juice, 4 Tbls. flour, 6 egg yolks and pineapple in a double boiler and cook until thick.
Spread between, layers, on top and sides of cake.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, mix pretzels in and pat in bottom of pan.
Bake ten minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool. While cooling, mix with mixer the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of pretzel crust and chill.
Mix strawberry jello with 2 cups boiling water, then add frozen strawberries and drained crushed pineapple.
Mix and pour on top of the other two layers.
Chill until set.

title: zucchini-mexican style
directions: *Diced and fried crisp bacon or crumbled, cooked sausage may be used.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Brown hamburger, then drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook about 10 minutes on medium-high.
Cap and clean peppers.
Salt the inside.
Stuff with mixture, leaving pepper whole or cut in halves.
Bake in oven 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle each with grated Cheddar before serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese until soft.
Beat in confectioners sugar and peanut butter; slowly add milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Cook pork picnic in crock-pot.
I cook mine about 17 hours on low.
Take out, clean off fat and bone.
Shred up meat.
Pour on sauce.
Put back in crock-pot for about 2 hours to simmer.

title: wine jelly
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup of water and add rest of ingredients.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Heat all ingredients except cucumbers.
When mixture boils, pour over cucumbers.
Let cool, then put in refrigerator.
Will keep up to a month.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown and simmer first 4 ingredients for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix altogether in a covered casserole. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: mozzarella and tomato salad
directions: On a large serving platter, alternate overlapping slices of tomatoes and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle basil, parsley and black olives over all.
Drizzle vinaigrette over salad and grind black pepper on generously.
Serve at room temperature.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pickled bologna
directions: Boil and pour over bologna which has been picked with a fork.

title: emmie's reese's cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and peanut butter.
Add in sugars, then eggs, vanilla and flour.
Roll into large balls and place inside mini-muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups together in container.
Add wine and mix together. Wash and prepare chicken pieces in baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: date nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together; add walnuts and dates.
In a separate bowl, combine the egg, milk and margarine; add to dry ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 3 x 4-inch greased loaf pan for one hour in a 375° oven.

title: homemade chili
directions: Saute beef in saucepan.
Add beef, onions, garlic, tomato sauce and seasonings to boiling water.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours with top off.
Add beans and cook another 1/2 hour slowly. Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, hot water, pineapple, bananas and blueberries; refrigerate and let gel. Mix last 4 ingredients to make topping. Spread on top of congealed salad and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients; stir in remaining ingredients just until moist.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pickled bologna
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 8 minutes. Cool and pour over bologna.
Keep refrigerated.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: kitchen klatter orange jello salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, water and orange juice; stir to dissolve Jell-O.
Add crushed pineapple, oranges and pineapple flavoring. Chill.
Make pudding as directed.
Add lemon flavoring and let cool.
Add whipped cream and spread over Jell-O.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Slowly add flour. Fold in flavorings and 7-Up.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in well-greased tube pan.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Turn out of pan.

title: spiced baked bananas(for diabetics)
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add pecans halves.
Bake in a 325° oven about 30 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from oven and drain on paper towels.

title: classical cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and spread into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread graham cracker crumbs over margarine. Layer evenly with butterscotch chips, chocolate chips, nuts and coconut.
Drizzle condensed milk on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, just until barely golden brown.
Cool in pan.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: venison oven steak
directions: Pound steaks out, flour them and brown in skillet on both sides until brown.
Season to taste.
Layer steaks on a lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Top with
can or two of cream of mushroom soup with enough Kitchen Bouquet to brown nicely.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until tender.
Simple and delicious.

title: rotel dip
directions: Chunk Velveeta in glass bowl; add Ro-Tel.
Cover with lid and microwave for 10 minutes.
Brown ground beef; drain and add to cheese and Ro-Tel.

title: oatmeal icebox cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and beat well.
Add sifted flour, soda and salt.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Refrigerate and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: custard pumpkin pie
directions: Combine egg and pumpkin.
Mix sugar with salt and spices and add to pumpkin mixture.
Blend in milk.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: hawaiian sandwich filling
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make 2 cups of filling.

title: marinated cube steaks
directions: Use large skillet with nonstick finish or coat regular skillet with vegetable spray-on for cookware.
Place meat in skillet. Pour dressing over meat and cover.
Let stand 20 minutes, turning once.
Brown meat in skillet over medium until done.
Add tomato. Season with salt.
Serve meat topped with tomato and pan juices. Makes 4 servings, 250 calories.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put one or two teaspoonfuls of tea into boiling water.
Stir and drink while warm.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients in the order they appear.
Bake 1 hour at 300°. You can use onion salt instead of onion; sprinkle on top and mix.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 6 x 10-inch dish. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg together with fork until crumbly and sprinkle over apples. Pour butter or shortening over apple mixture. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Can serve warm with cream.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter into a 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375° until golden brown.

title: million dollar rice salad
directions: Cream the cheese, sugar and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add rice, cherries, pineapple and marshmallows.
Fold in Dream Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix dry ingredients in oil.
Put crackers in a container that can be sealed.
Add oil mix; shake well.
Shake every 15 minutes for 2 hours.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add eggs and flour, mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: easy-time squares
directions: Mix all ingredients except pie filling.
Pour into well-greased 15 x 10 x 2-inch jelly roll pan.
Mark off into 20 squares.
Place 1 heaping tablespoonful pie filling in center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
While warm, dust with powdered sugar.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs for 7 minutes.
Let cool then peel off shell.
Cut eggs into 2 halves and take out yolks.
With a fork, break up yolks into fine pieces.
Add sugar, mustard and mayonnaise and stir until creamy.
Spoon mixture back into egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: glamour mushroom rice
directions: Saute onion in melted butter and put in 2-quart Pyrex dish. Then add other ingredients.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tomato soup
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour, sugar, salt, pepper and 1 cup tomato juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat and blend in 1 more cup of tomato juice and 2 cups milk. Heat until hot enough to serve.
Do not boil.

title: hot fruit ambrosia
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in 1 1/2-quart casserole in oven.
Remove, stir in flour, brown sugar and salt.
Add peaches, pineapple and cherries.
Toss lightly to combine.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake 10 additional minutes. May be served as is for brunch or topped with ice cream for dessert.
Serves 6.

title: pork n bean casserole
directions: Place layer of bread into 13 x 9 inch pan, then cover bread with layer of pork-n-beans and onions, if desired.
Then cover beans with layer of cheese.
Repeat this again and cover top with layer of bacon.
Bake at 350 degrees until bubbling.
If bacon is not cooked, broil until browned.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Sift flour.
Measure and add salt, soda and spices.
Sift again.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture and beat until smooth.
Chill dough in refrigerator for several hours. Divide chilled dough in 2 parts.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness and spread with the following filling.

title: shrimp thermidor
directions: Melt cream cheese and 1 stick oleo.
Saute shrimp, onion, pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons oleo.
Add soup, mushrooms rice and seasonings.
Stir in cream cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Place in casserole and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan ball cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Roll in small balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
While hot, roll balls in powdered sugar.

title: dream bars
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add coconut and nuts.
Spread on top of hot crust and return to oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Cut into bars.

title: white barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Use as a basting sauce while cooking meat on grill.
Sauce will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: sundae cake
directions: Bake Betty Crocker's sour cream white cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1 cup boiling water on wild strawberry Jell-O.
While still hot, poke holes in cake.
Spoon Jell-O slowly over cake. Chill.
Mix pudding according to directions; pour over cooled cake. Cover with 1 quart Cool Whip.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: cheddar cheese dressing(yields 1 quart)
directions: Mix well.
Set aside overnight so flavors mix.

title: cuban black beans(in a crock-pot)
directions: Place washed dried beans in crock-pot (do not soak beans). Pour boiling water over beans to cover with 2 inches.
Add salt pork or ham bone and bay leaves; cook on high for 4 hours or low for 8 hours, until tender, checking that beans remain covered.
Add water as needed.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 1 hour additional.
Serve over white rice or in a side bowl.
Serves 8.

title: chicken jubilee
directions: Flour chicken and brown in oven at 400° for about a half hour. Make sauce of chili sauce, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and juice from cherries.
Heat sauce and pour over chicken, saving half of sauce for basting.
Reduce oven heat to 300° to 325° and bake 1/2 to 3/4 hour longer, basting often.
Remove chicken to hot platter; add drained cherries and 1/2 cup sherry to sauce in pan. Heat about 5 minutes longer.

title: raspberry or strawberry butter
directions: The fruit and butter should be at room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add berries and refrigerate. Delicious on muffins.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Soak peas in cold water overnight or for several hours. Boil ham bone for about one hour. Add peas, onion, sugar, salt and pepper; cook 2 hours more or until peas are done. Add more water as needed. Also good using fresh peas and good without the onion.

title: pizza thins
directions: Cook meat and crumble.
Melt Velveeta in meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mound heaping tablespoon onto bread.
Freeze on cookie sheets.
Put into plastic bags and store in freezer.
Put in microwave to heat.

title: gumdrop fruit cake
directions: Sift flour and spices together.
Take 1 cup and roll with raisins and gumdrops in it.
Cream butter and sugar; add applesauce, soda, vanilla and other ingredients. Bake 2 hours in slow oven.

title: french fried cauliflower
directions: Soak cauliflower (head down) in cold salted water.
Drain until very dry on paper towel.
Break into flowerets.
Dip into mixture of egg, milk, salt and pepper, then dip into bread crumbs. Fry in oil until golden brown.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken until well done.
Debone.
Put meat back in broth.
Chop vegetables to desired size.
Combine all ingredients. Boil until well done.
Add water as necessary.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift flour with sugar, cocoa, salt, and baking soda.
Mix water and mayonnaise.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add flavoring. Stir in nuts.
Pour into two well-greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tests done.

title: dressing chicken
directions: Butter bottom of a large pan.
Place 1/2 cup of chicken on bottom.
Mix soup, bread, eggs and seasoning; put in half now, then rest of chicken and top with rest of bread and spices.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until brown.

title: mom's pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour batter into a well greased bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour or until toothpick inserted in the middle of the cake comes out clean.

title: punch for wedding
directions: Mix and blend all juices together.
Use any flavor of ice cream or sherbet if you desire to.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix together ingredients and thin with broth, adding salt and pepper as desired.
Pour over cooked noodles and bake until hot.

title: brie dessert round
directions: Cut around the top of the Brie 1/4-inch from the edge and remove top crust.
Place Brie in pretty baking/serving dish. Sprinkle nuts on top and drizzle with honey.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 15 minutes.
Serve immediately with your favorite crackers.

title: fudgy bonbon kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate chips and butter over low heat in a medium saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in condensed milk.
Stir in flour, nuts and vanilla until combined.

title: icebox pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool, then add the lemon juice. Chill milk until icy whip.
Add the sugar, then fold in Jell-O. Put in graham cracker shell.
Chill.

title: cocomoko float
directions: Mix all ingredients together except whipped cream.
Shake vigorously.
Pour into tall glass 1/4 filled with crushed ice. Beat well and top with a spoonful of whipped cream.

title: spinach squares
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients; spoon into greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute butter and onion until tender, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add 2 1/2 pounds chopped ham.
Can be frozen.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Mix thoroughly and spread.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas.
Spread mixture on tortillas.
Roll and have seam side down.
Refrigerate overnight and slice.

title: granny's italian delight
directions: Chop onion and green pepper. Saute onion and pepper. Add ground beef and brown lightly. Drain. Salt and pepper to taste. Add corn and soups. Cook slowly for 30 minutes to 1 hour. Cook the spaghetti in saltwater; drain. Pour sauce over noodles and mix. Place grated cheese over top. Put in oven at 375° until cheese melts. Serves 12.

title: shrimp and rice salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, salt, pepper, lemon juice and French dressing together in a small bowl; mix well.
Mix rice, olives, shrimp, onions and cauliflower in a large bowl.
Pour dressing mixture over shrimp mixture.
Mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, add salt, tomatoes, tomato paste, seasoned salt and garlic powder.
Combine remaining ingredients, except Cheddar cheese.
Put meat mixture into greased casserole dish and top with sour cream mixture, then top with Cheddar cheese.
Heat at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Sanitize a flowerpot and trowel.
Blend 1st four ingredients until smooth.
Add milk and instant pudding.
Put entire bag of Oreos in food processor.
Process until it looks like dirt.

title: homemade chocolate syrup
directions: Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil on medium heat for approximately 20 to 30 minutes until it thickens.
Serve on hot, buttered biscuits for breakfast.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg and milk; stir swiftly.
Melt margarine in iron skillet.
Pour batter into skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Combine all ingredients. Blend and chill until served.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Mix Swiss chocolate cake as directed.
Put 1/2 batter in bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream together; spread over platter.
Chop tomatoes, onions, green peppers and lettuce.
Layer over top of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle sharp or Cheddar cheese on top and use tortilla chips to dip.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Brown and drain the ground beef.
Mix all ingredients (except cheeses) together.
Simmer 10 minutes. Add cheeses.
Stir until mixed.
Keep warm and serve as a dip for crackers, etc.

title: greek egg custard
directions: Heat 1/2 the milk; add sugar, butter and all ferina.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Do not boil.
Keep mixing, but do not let it bubble.
When it gets thick, turn off heat and add the rest of the milk, then add the eggs.
Beat the eggs with the mixer until well mixed.
Bake at 350° until light brown on top.

title: light basting sauce for the grill
directions: Combine ingredients in tight glass jar.
Refrigerate till needed.
Shake well before using.
May be used for basting beef, pork, chicken or lamb.

title: crazy spaghetti
directions: Saute meat in heavy pot in its own fat and juices. Add onions and 1 ounce soy sauce. Stir and simmer until onions are soft. Add chopped cabbage and another 1 ounce soy sauce. Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes; stir. Add drained bean sprouts, mushrooms and remaining soy sauce. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Add cooked and drained spaghetti. Mix well. Serve hot.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until done.
Let cool.
Peel and slice.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Stir cheese with butter, milk and flour until melted.
Pour mixture over sliced potatoes, making sure to cover all potatoes. Bake at 350° until cheese mixture bubbles.

title: crabbies(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except muffins.
Spread mixture on muffin halves and freeze until cheese mix is set.
Cut into eighths and put in freezer bags.
Return to freezer until ready to serve.

title: pineapple cheesecake(heritage recipe)
directions: Boil pineapple, add Jello.
Set aside to cool and thicken slightly.
Cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Add to Jello, pineapple mixture.

title: big mouth sandwich
directions: Brown ground beef very thoroughly, drain well.
Stir in salt and chili powder, keep hot.
Halve, peel and slice the avocados into flat slices.
Split French Bread in half lengthwise, lightly toast cut sides under broiler.
Place half of the avocado slices on bottom half of bread.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Heat refried beans.
Spread an even layer of beans over the avocado, then spoon on browned meat.
Cover meat with shredded cheese, then with shredded lettuce.
Sprinkle lettuce with taco sauce if using. Cover with a layer of sliced tomato then sprinkle on the chopped onions.
Place remaining avocado slices on the tomatoes and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Cover with the top half of the bread, cut into serving sized sandwiches.

title: one pot spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is brown and onion tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in broth, tomato paste, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add spaghetti a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, boil gently, uncovered, for 15 to 17 minutes, or until spaghetti is tender, stirring frequently.
Serve with cheese.

title: diet divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add powdered milk; mix well. Add extract and Sweet 'N Low.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
Remove from a cookie sheet.
Dust with cinnamon.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter in large casserole dish.
Add crushed crackers. Stir to coat.
Remove 1/2 crackers and reserve for top.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all of the above in the mushroom soup on a low stove. Cook until the cream cheese is melted. At this time, it may be put in a mold pan or even a plain bowl. Refrigerate overnight. Remove from bowl and garnish with parsley and some more green onion slices. Serve with Wheat Thins or Triscuits.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients in a big bowl.
Let set in refrigerator about 1 hour and stir again before serving.

title: mock boursin au poivre
directions: Blend cream cheese with garlic, caraway, basil and dill weed. Pat into round flat shape.
Roll generously on all sides in lemon pepper.
Make a few days ahead.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: michigan sauce
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together and simmer in a saucepan for about 1 hour.
Serve as a sauce for hot dogs.

title: johnnycakes
directions: Add water or milk to whatever thickness you want.
Cook on hot, greased griddle pan until dark brown.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Bake chicken breasts (approximately 1 pound) with diced celery, onion, salt and pepper at 350° for 1 hour, or until tender.

title: pig-pickin' cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oranges (including juice), oil and eggs. Bake in three 8-inch layers as directed on cake mix box.
As soon as you take layers out of oven, spoon juice from pineapple over layers.
Mix Cool Whip, pudding and pineapple and frost cake between and on top of layers.
Refrigerate.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients together and set aside.

title: lamb with scallions and bamboo shoots
directions: Cut meat against the grain into 2 inches long and 1/8-inch thick slices.
Combine hoisin sauce, soy sauce, cornstarch, sherry and sugar in a separate mixing bowl and set aside.

title: diabetic cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased skillet or baking dish and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pineapple upside-down
directions: Drain pineapple overnight.
(Press occasionally with a fork.) Prepare cake according to directions.
Use pineapple juice in place of water.
Bake about 15 minutes in
a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool.

title: mudi's strawberry trifold
directions: Cut cake in half. Add half of ingredients, then rest (in order).
Put chopped nuts on top if desired.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Make a sauce of soups, tomatoes and broth.
Layer in a casserole, beginning with chicken, cheese, onion, Doritos and sauce.
Make 2 layers.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: joe denardo pasta sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter and olive oil.
Add garlic and anchovies; saute 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes (2 large cans), tomato sauce, basil, 2 tablespoons sweet pepper flakes (or fresh pepper), sugar, salt and pepper.
You may need very little salt because the anchovies give it a little salt.
Cook 50 minutes.
It is a thin sauce.

title: cherry enchiladas
directions: Spray 8 x 10-inch baking dish with Pam.
Spoon cherry pie filling in each tortilla and fold in dish with folded side down. In saucepan, add 1 cup water, sugar and margarine.
Bring to a boil and pour over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
I cover mine for 30 minutes with foil to keep the tortillas from getting hard and then uncover the last 15 minutes to brown. Serves 6.

title: old fashioned oatmeal pie
directions: In mixing bowl beat eggs.
Add honey, oats, brown sugar, butter and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until browned and knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients (except potatoes and carrots) thoroughly.
Pack firmly into a 9 x 4-inch loaf pan.

title: oven-baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Mix baking mix, paprika, salt and pepper. Coat chicken. Place in dish. (Dish and butter should be hot.) Bake 35 minutes; turn chicken and bake 15 minutes more or until well done.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: In a large bowl mix sugar, butter, milk, creme de menthe and creme de cacao until creamy.
Spread over brownies.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate (use the microwave for 1 minute on High, then stir).
Spread evenly over creme de menthe mixture. Chill for at least 3 hours.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cool pie shell first!
Melt chocolate and butter over double boiler.
Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Stir into chocolate.
Add milk slowly; continue stirring.
Cook until fully thickened (15 minutes).
Beat egg yolks well.
Take chocolate and mix in yolks. Beat thin.
Put in chocolate mix.
Cool about 1 minute, then remove from heat.
Cool partially and stir in vanilla, then put in pie shell.
Put meringue on top, then bake about 12 minutes at 350°.

title: butter pecan pound cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; beat 2 minutes, then add can of frosting. (Stir in; do not beat.) Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tested done. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or drizzle with caramel frosting.

title: frozen lemon squares
directions: Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar.
Press into 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, then ReaLemon.
Pour into crust.
Top with whipped topping.

title: apricot delight
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend well.
Serve on crackers like jelly or over low-fat ice cream.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine in large bowl 3 cups flour, sugar, dry milk powder, salt and yeast.
Add warm water to flour mixture and stir to make a batter.
Add remaining 2 cups flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover bowl and put in warm place to double in bulk, about 1/2 hour.
Stir down with a wooden spoon.
Add soda which has been dissolved in water.
Place batter in two large greased loaf pans.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 1/2 hour.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Bread must be toasted to obtain its full flavor.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mexi dip snack
directions: Cook and stir ground beef until brown.
Drain.
Stir in beans, tomato sauce, seasoning mix, onions, green peppers, mustard and chili powder. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Spread in pie plate.
Cool.
Top with sour cream, shredded lettuce and shredded cheese.
Makes enough for a party.
Serve with chips.

title: apple crisp parfaits
directions: In individual glasses, layer ice cream, apples, cereal and Mrs. Butterworths syrup.
Repeat layering, ending with syrup.
Top with whipped cream and half pecan or walnut garnish, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Spray 12-inch skillet with cooking spray.

In skillet, melt margarine.	Add potatoes, onion, salt, pepper and caraway seed. Cover and cook until potatoes are tender and brown, about 15 minutes, turning potatoes occasionally with pancake turner.
Remove skillet from heat.	Sprinkle potato mixture with cheese.
Cover skillet until cheese melts.

title: cabbage for a king
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling, salted water for 15 minutes.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour; add tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Toast in oven the buttered bread, cubed. Drain cabbage.
Grease 2 casseroles.

Put in layer of cabbage, layer of sauce, then bread cubes and cheese; layer cabbage again, sauce, bread cubes and cheese (make 2 or 3 layers). Bake at 375° for 30 minutes (15 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered).
Freezes well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon-lime salad
directions: In large bowl, stir boiling water into gelatins until completely dissolved.
Stir together mayonnaise, sour cream, cottage cheese, pineapple, horseradish and pecans.
Stir into gelatin mixture, mixing well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill several hours or until set.

title: garden vegetable soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in Dutch oven until brown; drain.
Stir in sauce mix, water, basil, salt, pepper and tomatoes (with liquid); break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally; 10 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and Veg-All (with liquid).
Cover and cook until macaroni is tender, 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Stir in parsley.
About 9 1/2 cups soup.

title: party wieners
directions: Place jelly and mustard in crock-pot.
Cook on high until well blended when stirred.
Cut wieners to desired size (about 3/4-inch pieces).
Add wieners to crock-pot.
Cook on high for several hours, until wieners are well cooked.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased casserole (Pam).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until tender and drain, reserving 1/4 c. of liquid.
Add mayonnaise to carrot liquid and mix well/
Put carrots into 9 X 13 casserole dish and pour mayonnaise mixture over carrots.
Sprinkle with flavored breadcrumbs.

title: mexican eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplants and slice thinly.
Cook in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Brown beef, onion and pepper in a large skillet.
Add flour, salt, pepper, oregano, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Mix well; cook until thickened.
In two 1 1/2-quart casserole baking dishes, mix layers of drained eggplant slices and meat mixture. Repeat and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8

title: mom's green salad
directions: *May use 1 package of Dream Whip prepared as directed.

title: cashew goodies
directions: In double boiler melt chips, add noodles and cashews.
Stir well just to cover noodles and cashews.
Drop on wax paper.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil chicken and dice.
Set aside in bowl.
Mix soups and chiles together; add small amount of broth to soup mixture.
Grease bottom and sides of baking dish.
Begin to layer ingredients: crushed chips, spoon on soup mixture, chicken and cheese.
Repeat layers until chicken is gone.
It doesn't usually take all of the soup, depending on how much chicken is used.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: taffy apple pie
directions: Boil unopened can of condensed milk in a large pan of water for 5 hours.
Make sure the can is always submerged.
In graham cracker crust, slice apple with skin.
Pour taffy from condensed milk over apple slices.
Sprinkle with chopped nut topping.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix in pie pan.
Spread with fingers.
Fill with your choice of filling.

title: 7-minute fat-free frosting
directions: Combine sugar, water, cream of tartar and salt in a saucepan. Bring to boiling, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Very slowly add sugar syrup to the egg whites in a bowl.
Beat constantly with a hand mixer until stiff peaks form, about 7 minutes.
Yields frosting for 2 (8 or 9-inch) layers or one 10-inch tube cake.

title: apple butter nut bread
directions: Sift
flour,
baking
powder,
soda and spices together. Cream oil,
eggs and sugar.
Add apple butter, raisins and nuts to the oil,
eggs and sugar.
Then add the sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour
into
a
9 x 5-inch loaf pan.	Bake in a 375° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Then add both cans of corn and macaroni.
Stir well, then add cheese. Bake, covered, with foil for 1/2 hour, then uncovered for an additional 1/2 hour.

title: banana split refrigerator cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13x9x2in pan. Prepare, bake, and cool cake according to directions.
Combine topping mix, pudding mix, milk, and vanilla extract in large bowl. Beat at medium speed until stiff.
Spread over cooled cake. Place cherry, banana slices, pineapple pieces, and nuts randomly on top and drizzle with fudge.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: meat balls supreme
directions: Soften bread in milk; add egg.
Mix meats.
Add onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Combine mixtures; form into balls. Roll in flour.
Brown in fat.
Add tomato juice and Kitchen Bouquet.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add water, carrots and celery. Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Add peas; cook until peas are hot through.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 3 minutes.
Stir while boiling.
Take off heat. Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until peanut butter has melted.
Add oatmeal.
Drop on waxed paper by spoonfuls.
May be eaten warm or cold.

title: crock-pot barbecued ribs
directions: Spread ribs on cookie sheet; salt and pepper them.
Place in oven at 400° for 35 minutes or until browned.
Place ribs in crock-pot and pour on remaining ingredients.
Cook on high for 2 hours or on low for 6 hours.
These are not greasy.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Bone and skin chicken breast; cut into 1-inch cubes.
Mix pancake mix, salt and pepper; add water until creamy batter consistency.
Heat canola oil in skillet to 375°.
Add chicken to batter; stir and begin dropping battered chicken cubes into hot oil.
Turn after golden brown on one side.
Remove after other side is golden brown and drain on plate with paper towel.
After all chicken is fried, put in a bowl.
Heat soup with water added until gravy thickens; add soy sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with onions and cashews.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: low-fat chocolate pie
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Add Cool Whip and pour into 9-inch baked pie shell. Top with crushed cookies.
Fat-free and guilt free.

title: shrimp perlew
directions: Fry bacon and break into tiny pieces.
In same pan saute the bell pepper, celery, onions and salt and pepper until it becomes clear.
Add raw rice, hot water and the shrimp.
Simmer slowly, covered, about 30 minutes.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Mix oil with vinegar, water, lemon juice, garlic and seasoning.
In large salad bowl with tight fitting lid, toss the oil mixture with the broccoli.
Let marinate all day or overnight, tossing the mixture several times before eating.
Refrigerate.

title: don's favorite pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine all of the ingredients thoroughly. Add pecans last to mixture.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Pie is done when outer edge of filling is set and center slightly soft.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Then add cold water.
Drain fruit cocktail, reserving juice.
Add fruit to jello.
Pour half of this mix into an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish to form first layer of salad.
Chill.

title: carter's breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; remove from pan and drain.
Saute mushrooms and onion; drain.
In a large bowl, mix together milk, eggs, mustard, chives and soup.
Add bread and 1 cup cheese; mix.
Add sausage, mushrooms and onion; stir.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.

title: rice krispies treat
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan on low heat.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down with spatula.
Let cool and cut with a sharp knife.

title: sweet-and-sour beef
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet.
Brown beef on all sides. Add salt, tomatoes, brown sugar, vinegar, onion and bay leaf. Cover skillet.
Lower heat.
Le simmer for 2 hours, until beef is tender.
Add pepper strips to beef.
Cook 10 minutes to blend all flavors.
Serve with rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: caesar salad
directions: Stir together in order lettuce, oil, Worcestershire sauce, cheese, salt, pepper, egg, lemon juice and garlic.
Toss.
Add bread cubes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill 1 hour and stir before serving.
May be served in a bread bowl or with crackers.

title: broccoli beef casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy sugared almond appetizers
directions: Cook in a non-stick skillet for 5 to 7 minutes on medium heat.
Cool on wax paper and break apart.
Enjoy!

title: easy cheese straws
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Mix together cheese and pie crust mix until well blended.
On a lightly floured board, roll out to about 1/8 inch thick and cut into any shape you desire. Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: scallops
directions: Pour melted margarine and orange juice into a baking dish. Add scallops.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no fat vegetable soup
directions: Vegetables can be fresh or frozen.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Chop sausage, onion and bell pepper in skillet.
Cook and brown, then drain off grease.
Add soup, rice and pimentos.
Mix together.
Put in pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese on top.

title: german chocolate frosting original recipe
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans; beat until spreading consistency.
Makes enough frosting to cover a 3-layer cake.

title: milk rice(arroz con leche)
directions: Soak rice in hot water for 15 minutes.
Wash rice in cold water.
Cook in 2 cups of water and cinnamon.
When water has evaporated, add sugar and milk until it boils.
When rice is cooked, add lightly beaten yolks.
Boil for a few minutes and serve in large plate garnished with raisins.

title: cheese and potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, soup, milk and 1/2 of the onion rings.
Pour into well-greased crock-pot. Cook on low for 7 to 9 hours. Sprinkle rest of onion rings on top when done.

title: chicken divan
directions: Wash and simmer chicken, covered in salted water until chicken is very tender.
Remove chicken and reserve broth.
Debone chicken and cut into long, thin slices.

title: quick caramel icing
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients, stirring until sugar is dissolved, then cook without stirring until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat until begins to thicken.
Add vanilla and 1 tablespoon cream or milk.
Continue to beat until ready to spread.

title: all-american bean bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, lightly brown sliced franks with onion, butter, mustard, allspice and pepper, mixing well. Pour beans into a baking dish.
Add catsup and brown sugar; mix well.
Spread evenly over the bottom of the dish.
Layer franks over the beans.
Top with cheese, if desired.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cauliflower with cheese sauce
directions: Bring 1 inch of water to a boil with 1/2 teaspoon salt in a medium saucepan; add cauliflower.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes until crisp-tender.
Drain and keep warm.

title: scalloped cheese tomatoes
directions: Place all ingredients in shallow baking dish in alternating layers.
Bake 1/2 hour in moderate oven at 350°.

title: "no fail" pie crust
directions: Slightly beat egg and add the vinegar, water and salt.
Mix in shortening and add flour.
Roll out on floured table.

title: whole baked chicken
directions: Rinse chicken.
Place on baking dish.
Sprinkle oregano, garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Coat chicken with olive oil. Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn chicken occasionally while cooking (3 or 4 times).

title: herb mint sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients except oil in blender at high speed. Add oil and blend until well emulsified.

title: magic marshmallow crescent puffs
directions: Hidden marshmallow melts like magic and has a hollow puff.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Melt chocolate morsels and butterscotch morsels in top of double boiler.
Add peanuts and noodles.
Spoon onto cookie sheet covered with waxed paper.
Refrigerate until hard.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir onion, pepper and mushrooms until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except spaghetti.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Make spaghetti noodles.

title: herbed new potatoes
directions: Peel a 1/2-inch strip around center of each potato.
Cook potatoes, covered in boiling water, for 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients, tossing well to coat.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Combine cheese, sugar and flour, mix well.
Add pineapple juice then pineapple.
Crumble Ritz crackers over top of mixture.

title: cake (plain)
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg and vanilla and beat for 1 minute.
Set aside.
Sift together baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Add raisins.
Place in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: linguine with tuna sauce
directions: Combine tomatoes, oil, parsley, onions and basil.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Grate lemon rind.
Sprinkle over tuna with lemon juice. Toss with pepper.
Add to tomato mixture and cook for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add to cooked linguine.

title: shrimp and sausage toss
directions: Put casserole dish in oven with 1 tablespoon butter at 200°. Fry sausage with 3 tablespoons butter and 1 clove minced garlic. Boil vermicelli; drain.
Toss all ingredients in warm casserole and serve.

title: peanut-raisin-cocoa chews
directions: Combine peanut butter, raisins, honey, cocoa and vanilla in a bowl; stir until well blended.
Spread chopped nuts, crushed cereal or shredded coconut in flat pan or dish; drop cocoa mixture by teaspoonfuls and roll into desired coating until well covered. Chill.
Makes about 30 candies.
You get more if you make them smaller.

title: special cereal bars
directions: Place corn syrup, sugar and butter in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Combine with cereal.

title: tasty chip dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well, then refrigerate.

title: curried pecans
directions: Combine oil, curry powder, Worcestershire sauce and cayenne pepper in skillet.
Heat until well blended.
Add nuts. Stir until well coated. Line a cookie sheet with brown paper and spread nuts evenly over pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for 10 minutes. Store in an airtight container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread chicken (after deboned) in a buttered casserole dish. Mix soup and sour cream well and pour over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers fine.
Spread over the top of chicken.
Melt margarine and dribble over the top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown beef in hot oil.
Add onion and celery and cook until liquid is clear.
Add beans, tomatoes and rest of ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.
Layer cabbage and meat in greased casserole. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: paper cup frozen salad
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, sugar, salt, pineapple, bananas and food coloring; mix well.
Fold in nuts and cherries. Place 12 cupcake papers in muffin tins.
Spoon mixture into cups evenly.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze.

title: chicken dinner bake
directions: Combine soup mix and 1 1/2 cups water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add mushroom liquid and milk. In a large skillet, melt butter.
Cook onions until tender, but not brown.
Blend flour, salt and pepper.
Add soup mixture; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add mushrooms, chicken (cut up), peas and pimiento.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: favorite pecan pie
directions: Note:
1 1/2 cups chopped pecans can be used.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add broth, sauce, cumin, chili powder, jalapeno, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add chicken and tomato; cook for 5 minutes.

title: pepperoni casserole
directions: Cook seashells until tender, but firm; drain.
Mix heated spaghetti sauce with macaroni.
Add 1/2 of the pepperoni.
Mix Parmesan cheese through.
Add 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in buttered casserole and top with remaining Mozzarella and pepperoni.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blonde brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine melted shortening and brown sugar. Stir in eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread into a greased 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Let cool and then cut into squares.

title: pita chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut pita bread along the folded circumference to create four circles of bread.
Combine olive oil and garlic.
Lightly brush on the outside of the bread.
Stack the circles of bread and cut into pie shaped wedges.
Arrange in a single layer on a nonstick baking sheet.
Bake until golden, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve with your favorite dip.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with turkey or chicken.

title: brown gravy for beef
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan.
Add flour to margarine and stir until dark brown. Pour over beef stew already cooked.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, sugar, salt and cocoa into ungreased cake pan (13 x 9-inch).
Make 3 holes.
Pour oil in large hole, vinegar in medium hole and vanilla in small hole.
Cover with water and stir well with fork.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: best onion rings
directions: Dip onion slices in flour, then in egg whites and back in flour again.
Drop in hot shortening and fry until golden brown.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and flour.
Add boiling water.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add some hot mixture to beaten egg yolks, then add yolks to flour mixture.
Add butter, lemon juice and rind until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cool.
Use egg whites to make meringue.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Roll dough thin on floured board. Cut with desired shape cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes on lightly greased cookie sheet or until lightly browned.

title: crisp potato skins
directions: Hollow out baked potato skins, using inside for creamed or sauteed potatoes, then cut into long strips.
Butter thoroughly. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and place in 375° to 400° oven until crisp.
They may be served with Ranch dip or by themselves.

title: scallop potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes about 10 or 15 minutes; peel and slice.
Place potatoes in well-buttered casserole dish.
Spread with some pimento (optional).

title: cabbage and onion
directions: Cook bacon over medium-high heat until crisp. Remove and drain on paper towel. Crumble into bits and set aside. Stir bell pepper and onion into hot bacon grease until softened. Stir in cabbage and stir. Increase heat to high. Stir-fry until cabbage is tender. Season with black pepper. Remove from pan and sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Add French onion soup and cook for 10 minutes on low.
Add salt and pepper.
Place in greased shallow baking dish.
Cover top with bread crumbs, shredded cheese and paprika.

title: holiday cranberry punch
directions: Combine fruit juice and bourbon.
Refrigerate until chilled. Just before serving, pour in ginger ale.

title: heart-shaped cake
directions: Prepare favorite white cake recipe or boxed cake mix and divide batter between 1 (8-inch) square pan and 1 (8-inch) round pan.
Bake according to directions.
Remove cakes from pan and cool.

title: betsy's favorite chicken and stuffing
directions: Put cooked chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the soup and milk.
Pour over the chicken.
Put prepared dressing on top of chicken.
Mix broth and melted margarine; pour over stuffing.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, covered, and 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine liquid ingredients.
Combine dry ingredients, adding to liquids along with zucchini.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put hash browns in bowl; stir in 1 stick melted margarine. Mix in cheese, sour cream, soup, salt and pepper.
Put in 9 x 11-inch casserole.
Mix together bread crumbs and 1 stick melted margarine.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage cornbread bake
directions: Mix Jiffy cornbread mix as directed.
Pour in creamed corn. Brown pork sausage; drain grease.
Pour 1/2 can cornbread mix in a greased baking dish.
Add sausage and cheese.
Pour remaining mixture in.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats, brown sugar and buttermilk in bowl; let stand 10 minutes.
Sift together dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add egg and oil to oatmeal mixture; mix well.
Add oatmeal mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins, filling each two-thirds full.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until done.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: hungarian goulash soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook bacon until almost crisp.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add beef cubes and brown on all sides.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt, pepper and sugar. Stir and cook for 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
About 1/2 hour before serving, add the potatoes and cook until tender. Garnish each serving with a dollop of sour cream, if desired. Yields 8 servings (about 2 quarts).

title: pineapple salad
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and flour.
Stir and add pineapple juice. Cook in double boiler until thickened.
Mix marshmallows, nuts and pineapple chunks in a bowl.
Cool sauce and pour over mixture in bowl.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients until creamy.
Add dry ingredients. Blend well.
Stir in uncooked oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: lemon-cream tea loaf
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter, creaming well.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating mixture well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in pecans.

title: bran muffins
directions: Add juices, apples, vanilla and pineapple to mixture.
Beat egg whites (not stiff).
Fold into the mixture and allow to stand 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apple or peach cobbler
directions: Place apples or peaches in bottom of greased deep-dish pie plater or baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar. Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and butter.
Add dry ingredients all at once to milk mixture.
Mix until smooth. Pour over fruit.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Preheat oven to 320°.
Bake slow for about 50 minutes.
Great with ice cream.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Put in oven-safe bowl.
Fry bacon. Remove bacon and save.
Fry onions in bacon fat until tender, not browned.
Mix sugar and mustard; add to onions.
Add beaten egg to vinegar and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add bacon and egg slices.
Mix lightly.
Heat at 250° for 30 minutes.
When ready, top with parsley.

title: low country marinated shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl (except shrimp). Add shrimp.
Make sure all shrimp are covered by the mixture. Cover the bowl and place in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with cole slaw or potato salad. Great for picnics or cookouts.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Makes 20 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If potatoes are frozen, it may take a bit longer.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in dish and let set.
Then spread 1/2 pint of sour cream on top.
Pour rest of jello mixture on top and let set.

title: chicken roll-ups(serve with acini de pepe)
directions: Use seasoning to suit taste.

title: beef stir fry
directions: Combine sesame oil and five spice powder in a skillet or wok and heat to medium high heat and brown and remove from pan. Meanwhile, combine soy sauce, cornstarch, beef broth and red pepper flakes and set aside. Heat vegetable oil in skillet or wok and brown ginger, garlic and onion. Add bean sprouts and snow peas and cook for several minutes. Add beef broth mixture and beef and heat until mixture starts to thicken. Serve with rice or noodles. We made this with rice noodles that we cooked in the wok after the beef.

title: black walnut cream cake
directions: Whip cream until stiff.
Drop in whole egg and mix well.
Add sugar, a small amount at a time.
Add salt and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add by hand to first mixture, a little at a time, stirring vigorously after each addition is made. Add the cup of black walnuts.

title: nonnie's waffles
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Mix with electric mixer until smooth. Preheat waffle iron, sprayed with PAM. Cook until golden brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Add Cool Whip.
Layer pan with pudding, then cookies, then cut up bananas.
Top with cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs until light and fluffy. Spoon in flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in bananas, lemon juice and pecans. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pie
directions: Put in graham cracker crust.
Put in a bowl the crushed pineapple.
Do not drain the pineapple.
Add the instant pudding, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: mock meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, but onion, garlic and broth.
Then add onion, garlic and broth.
Mix well.
Turn onto greased loaf pan and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: hominy salad
directions: Drain hominy and add all ingredients.
Chill well.
Serve on lettuce; garnish with tomato wedges.
Add more mayonnaise, if desired.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and dry with paper towels.
Blend together remaining ingredients.
Dip chicken pieces into coating mixture, covering all areas.
Arrange chicken pieces in shallow baking pan (13 x 9-inches).
Start baking at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° until done (about 40 minutes more).

title: potato rolls
directions: Soften active dry yeast in warm water.
Combine potatoes, shortening, sugar, salt and hot milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add softened yeast and egg.
Stir in 2 cups of the flour; beat well. Stir in remaining flour (or enough to make a soft dough).
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic (6 to 8 minutes).
Cover; let double (1 hour) in a warm place.
Punch down.
Shape in a ball, cover and let rise 10 minutes.
Make into rolls and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 1 hour.
