Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: harvest soup
directions: In heavy soup kettle, bring water to a boil.
Add all ingredients.
Return to boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring frequently to break up squash and form thick stock.
This soup can be made in large quantities, great left over and freezes well.

title: homemade chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together chicken, onion, celery, Veg-All, eggs, broth and soup and pour in a dish.
Then mix together the flour and the milk and melted oleo.
Pour over first mixture, then bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch pan and freeze overnight.

title: mushroom roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Separate crescent rolls and spread mushroom mixture on each piece.
Cut each crescent roll into 3 pieces.
Roll up each piece to triangle point.
Bake at 400° on greased cookie sheet for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate croissants
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate roll dough. Slice candy bars carefully into halves lengthwise. Brush rolls with melted
butter. Place candy slice at wide end of each triangle. Roll as for jelly roll.
Place on baking sheet.
Brush with butter.
Bake for 12 minutes or until brown.
Sprinkle the confectioners sugar lightly over hot croissants.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 8 servings.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: Measure dry ingredients and sift together.
Add to dry ingredients the diced bananas (measured), oil, vanilla, eggs, crushed pineapple with juice and nuts.
Stir to blend.
Do not beat.
Pour into a greased 9-inch tube pan or 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool on rack before removing from pan.

title: pile of pudding stuff
directions: 1st. Layer:
Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add nuts and flour (knead).
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.

title: easy fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook any type noodles as directed.
Drain.
Add half of a 1/2 pint whipped cream and stir into noodles.
Add pepper and Parmesan cheese, stirring as you pour in.
Mix well until cheese is melted and coats noodles.
Serve 2 as a meal or 4 as a side dish.

title: corn bread
directions: Grease pan.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour batter in pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Use an 8 or 9-inch baking pan.

title: rigg's noodles
directions: Mix eggs and milk, then add self-rising flour to mixture until it becomes sticky and thick.
Roll dough out thin and cut in strips.
Leave laid out to dry.
Cook noodles in choice of broth.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Heat over 450°.
Mix flour, soda, sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in sour cream.
Turn dough onto lightly flowered surface.
Lightly knead.
Roll dough 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with floured cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 10 - 12 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen - 2 inch biscuits.

title: zucchini wonton rolls
directions: Prepare zucchini and carrots first.
Let sit in cheesecloth and salt lightly.
Squeeze and drain out excess water for at least 40 minutes.

title: strawberry angel
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as package directs, using 1 cup minus 2 tablespoons cold milk, 2 tablespoons strawberry juice, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/8 teaspoon almond extract.
Fold in drained strawberries.
Spread on the top and sides of two 8-inch white layer cake.
Chill.
Store in refrigerator.
Serves 12.

title: baked vegetable rotini
directions: Prepare rotini according to package directions.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain rotini and place in large bowl.
Add all vegetables and stir.
Add in all seasonings into pimento cashew cheese.
Add this mixture to bowl of rotini and vegetables and stir in gently, but thoroughly.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with soy Mozzarella.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pear honey
directions: Keep your heart free from hate, your mind free from worry. Live simply, expect little, and give much.
Sing often, pray always.
Fill your life with love; scatter sunshine.
Forget self, think of others.
Do as you would be done by.
These are the tried links of contentments golden chain.

title: yellow angel food cake
directions: Add part of water to egg yolks and beat until lemon colored. Add baking powder, sugar, an the rest of the water.
Now add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add flavoring, if desired.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: noodles
directions: Work in flour and let stand in Fix-N-Mix for 10 minutes.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender; drain.
Add carrots to food processor bowl.
Add butter and rest of ingredients and process until smooth.
Spoon into 2 lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dishes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done, set and lightly brown.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together and drain.
Add chili seasoning, pepper, tomatoes (I use diced tomatoes), juice (I use Hunt's), beans and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add catsup and simmer for an hour.
Makes approximately 4 quarts.

title: gingerbread cookies(don't have to chill before rolling out.)
directions: (Dough can be chilled for 2 days.)

title: string pie
directions: Mix sauce and browned hamburg.
Put 1/2 of mixture in pie dish.
Put cooked spaghetti on top.
Spread cheese mixture on top. Cover with remainder of sauce.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil chicken until tender.
Break chicken into small pieces and place in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Add chopped bell pepper, onions, Doritos or Fritos, Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream of mushroom and chicken soups. Pour over mixture.	Top with shredded cheese and cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: dill pickles
directions: Fill enough jars to fill cooker with ingredients.
Put on lids.
Place jars in cooker with water just over the lids.
Bring to good boil.
Remove jars and place in sun for 8 hours.
Ready to use in 2 weeks.

title: filling for blueberry pie
directions: Mix and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: happy marriage recipe
directions: Fist put in some students in a classroom.

title: chicken balls
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into balls about the size of a marble. Makes about 20 balls.
Dip in egg and bread crumbs.
Chill.
Toast at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: glazed apricot chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place chicken in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Spread mixture over chicken.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Bone chicken and cut into small pieces; set aside.
Reserve broth. Combine stuffing mix and butter. Reserve 1/4 cup for garnish. Combine chicken soup with 1/2 the broth.
Mix mushroom soup with other half of broth.
Spoon 1/2 of stuffing mix in 13 x 9-inch baking dish that has been greased.
Top with 1/2 the chicken. Cover with 1/2 the chicken and chicken soup mix.
Layer rest of dressing mix, chicken and mushroom soup.
Sprinkle top with reserved 1/4 dressing. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin-nut bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; set aside. Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Add pumpkin and mix well. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with water. Mix well. Add mincemeat and pecans. Spoon into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pans. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Yields 2 loaves.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Dissolve cubes in water.
Add veggies and simmer until done. While cooking, in another pan melt 1 cup butter and mix flour, onion salt, Accent and garlic salt.
Add 2 quarts water and cheese whip.
Blend and add to other mixture.
Stir and heat and serve. Serve with cornbread.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa. Add shortening and milk. Boil several minutes to soft ball stage. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and beat immediately until thick enough to spread.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Pour off drippings.
Add Ragu sauce, mixing well and simmering.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs and Mozzarella cheese in bowl, mixing until smooth.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheese mixture alternately in 9 x 13-inch baking dish until all ingredients are used.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, at 325°
for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Combine oats, flour and sugar; cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Place 1/2 mixture in bottom of a buttered 8-inch square baking dish, spoon in pie filling, then spread remaining crumb mixture over the top.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm.
Spoon into sauce dishes and top with cream or ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic. Add and mix the tomatoes, mushroom soup, cooked noodles and taco seasoning.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour or until fork comes out clean.
Bake in 2 pans, one with warm water.
Cool and serve.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown meat in skillet; add taco seasoning.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk, corn, onion and pepper.
Heat shortening in skillet.
Add half of the corn bread mixture and layer of meat and cheese.
Add other half of corn bread and last layer of meat and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Bake pork chops plain for 30 minutes, then add all of the ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: picante dip
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well in blender.
Place in shallow dish.
Just before serving, top with the remaining ingredients.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Begin to cut avocado in half.
When the knife hits the seed, rotate the knife around the avocado until the avocado is halved. Spoon out avocado halves.
Mix all ingredients with potato masher until slightly lumpy.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large container.
Store in containers with lids.
Put desired amount into cup and add boiling water.

title: fried chicken
directions: Preheat shortening in a frying pan.
Mix eggs, salt, garlic salt, onion salt, pepper and lemon juice in a mixing bowl and mix 10 seconds.
Pour flour in bag.
Place chicken in the mixing bowl and cover with mixture.
Shake the chicken in flour.
Place chicken in frying pan and fry until golden brown.
Repeat until all chicken is fried, turning twice.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add bananas and eggs.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: date and chocolate cake
directions: Combine dates and boiling water.
Cool to room temperature. Mix together shortening and sugar, creaming until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs, adding one egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with date mixture, beating well after each addition.
Spread batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips and walnuts on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut in squares and may be topped with whipped cream.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar,
cornstarch	and
salt
until thick. Remove from heat; stir
in
jello	and butter until dissolved. Cool. Pour over
sliced strawberries in pie shell.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Top with whipped topping.

title: pita bread
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Let stand covered at room temperature for 1 hour.
Cut pita bread in half and then tear open. Spread the butter mixture on inside and put on baking sheet.
Cook in oven for 5 minutes or until crisp at 450°.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, sour cream and soup.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over top of mixture. Drizzle melted butter on top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Longer time may be needed, if in a deep dish.

title: double raspberry delight
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin in large bowl, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Add raspberries and pineapple juice; stir until berries are thawed and gelatin is slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Fold in banana.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve, topped with whipping cream, if desired.

title: new orleans potatoes
directions: Cook the potatoes in water for 15 to 20 minutes. Drain off water. Combine all ingredients except margarine and crumbs.
Place in long pan. Drizzle margarine on top and sprinkle corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lazy man's coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on the box.
While hot, punch holes in the cake with a teaspoon and pour the Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Let the cake cool completely.
Spread with whipped cream and sprinkle with coconut.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix cooked squash with onions, chopped fine.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix.
Line dish with crumbs.
Mix other ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes a large casserole.

title: snacks
directions: Melt together and pour over cereals.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours. Stir once or twice.

title: no crust fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour together.
Melt butter and chocolate together; add vanilla and salt.
Combine the 2 mixtures, stir and pour into a 9 inch buttered pie tin.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until when you touch the middle of the pie, it springs back.
Cut into wedges and top with vanilla or peppermint stick ice cream topped with hot fudge topping.
Serves 8.

title: dirt pie
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl; add pudding mix.
Beat with a wire whisk until well blended.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Stir in 1 cup of the cookies and the "rocks" into the pudding mixture.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.

title: chicken pie
directions: Start early enough according to time needed.
Place cubed chicken in baking dish.
Reserve small amount of stock in which to precook onion and garlic.
Also mix flour with 1/2 cup stock in small jar with lid until free of lumps.
Add to stock in pan; add salt and pepper.
Cook until thickened.
Add precooked onion, garlic and Veg-All.
Pour into baking dish with chicken already placed in the bottom.
Dot with butter (can omit if stock already has sufficient fat).
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then gently place risen rolls on top of chicken pie and return to the oven for 15 more minutes or until the rolls are well browned.

title: microwave banana nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in a large mixing bowl. Stir in bananas, nuts and then remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch glass loaf dish. Cook for 6 to 7 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes. Turn out onto cooling rack.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: chicken salad waldorf
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add chicken, apples, celery and nuts.
Mix well.
Serve on lettuce.
Garnish with apple slices and celery leaves, if desired.

title: mint-glazed lamb chops
directions: For glaze, in a small saucepan, combine mint jelly, wine or orange juice, orange peel and pepper.
Heat until smooth.
Trim fat from meat.
Preheat grill.
Adjust heat for direct cooking. Place lamb chops on grill rack over medium heat.
Cover and grill for 10 to 16 minutes or until desired doneness, turning once halfway through and brushing with glaze often.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Stir together pecans and coconut and put on bottom of pan. Then add half of cake mix.
(Mix cake as directed on box.)
Mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese and margarine and pour over cake mix.
Add second half of cake mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift together dry ingredients; cut in shortening. Add yeast and buttermilk to dry ingredients. Knead dough to hold together.
Chill dough, covered with a towel. Put in refrigerator for 8 hours or overnight. Roll out dough about 1/2-inch thick and cut into rounds with 2-inch biscuit cutter. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil, then mash potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350°
until set, 30 minutes or more.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Chop dried beef.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Serve with raw vegetables and/or toast rounds.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add pumpkin.
Gradually beat in flour, salt, baking powder, soda and spices.
Mix well and add nuts.
Put in two bread pans.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Cool, peel and coarsely shred. Mix all
ingredients and turn into 2 quart buttered casserole. Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add shortening, salt, sugar, egg, cocoa and 1 cup flour.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in remaining flour.
Blend well.
Cover and let rise until double in size (about 1 hour).
Stir down by beating 25 strokes.
Turn dough onto floured board.
Roll out to 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread with butter and cinnamon sugar mixture.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Roll up and cut into 12 pieces.
Let rise until double (about 40 minutes).
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Top with milk and powdered sugar glaze.

title: zesta sausage casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let stand while mixing topping.

title: uncle woody's goolish
directions: Layer bottom of 9-inch casserole dish with meat.
Layer sliced potatoes, onions, potatoes, onions, salt and pepper throughout, until filled.
Top with peeled tomatoes.

title: drunkin biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients and put into 16 greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° approximately 15 minutes or until golden.

title: cranberry catsup(from wild alaska cranberries)
directions: Put cranberries in heavy saucepan with enough water to cover and boil until berries are soft (about 5 minutes). Drain and put berries through food mill. Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer in saucepan for 3 minutes; then add butter and let melt. Serve at room temperature or put in jars in refrigerator until ready to serve. Makes 1 pint.

title: carrot cake elite
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, baking soda and spices in a large bowl.

Combine carrots, oil, pineapple, eggs and water. Stir into dry ingredients, mixing until smooth. Stir in walnuts and raisins. Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. When cool, frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes(for crock-pot or slow cooker)
directions: Put half of ham, potatoes and onions in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; add grated cheese.
Repeat with remaining ham.
Spread undiluted soup over top.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
(High, 4 hours.) Ingredients may be increased by half for the 5-quart slow cooker.

title: wedding punch
directions: Soften sherbet in fruit juices and water.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Pour over large block of ice in punch bowl. Punch will bubble effectively during early part of serving.
Dry ice substitute for ice block will give a smoking effect.
Brighter green color may be obtained by adding food coloring.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 8 minutes in boiling water.
Drain.
Mix mushroom soup, mayonnaise, onion, cheese and egg with broccoli. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Sprinkle the salt over the first 3 ingredients and let set 1 hour; drain.
Boil the remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Pour over cucumbers and freeze in containers until ready to use.

title: greek twist cookies(makes approximately 75 cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add orange juice and 3 eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Roll 1 tablespoon of dough with hands into a 6-inch string.
Fold in half and twist.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 375°
for 25 minutes
until lightly browned. Remove from sheet immediately.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove tops, membranes and seeds from peppers.
Mix all other ingredients and fill peppers.
If any mixture is left, form into 2-inch balls and place all in a baking dish or small roaster pan. Cover with the sauce of your choice (I use Prego*).
Spoon sauce over peppers during baking period.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually, then egg.
Add applesauce and molasses.
Add flour, sifted with soda, salt and spices.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake in cake or bread pan for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: peppercorn dip
directions: Crush peppercorns.
Combine crushed peppercorns with cream cheese, milk, lemon juice and garlic powder.
Beat with an electric mixer using medium speed until smooth.
Makes 10 (2 tablespoon) servings.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers, leaving them whole.
Mix salt with enough water to cover pickles in a 5-gallon churn.
Mash pickles down under the water.
Let set for 6 or 7 days.
Take the pickles out of salt water and wash well.
Slice pickles.
Dissolve alum with enough water to cover the pickles in the churn.
Let set 6 hours. Take pickles out and wash well.
Cover pickles with vinegar. Place spices in a white rag and put in the churn with the vinegar. Let set 6 hours and pour out vinegar.
Layer pickles with sugar. Stir to dissolve the sugar.
Let set for 2 or 3 days.
Place pickles in jars.
Jars do not have to seal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Pour into large greased casserole. Top with dry stuffing mix.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: montgomery pie(also called farmer pie)
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onions, oregano, garlic and bell pepper. Add 1 cup water, paste and sauce.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: granddad's eastern shore sweet pone
directions: Scald in a saucepan the corn meal with the boiling water, stirring constantly.
Mix in flour, brown sugar, molasses and salt. Pour in cold water and stir to get out most lumps.
Bake overnight very slowly at low temperature, 200°.
Bake either in crock-pot or in a cast-iron or other heavy container in oven.

title: david's barbecue sauce
directions: Cook everything for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: frozen mint salad
directions: Mix pineapple, jello, and marshmallows. Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours then add mints and cool whip. Place in a 9 x 13 pan and freeze.

title: nacho dip
directions: Melt cheese.
Add chili and taco sauce.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: cauliflower - carrot - broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Chop up all your vegetables. Bring to a boil and cook until tender. Melt 1/2 cup butter in a pan. Put bread cubes in the butter, making sure that all the cubes are covered good with butter. Set aside.

title: party time chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts in dressing mix and butter or margarine. Mix cream of mushroom soup with cream cheese and dry white wine in blender.
Spread over chicken breasts. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk, and margarine on high for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every few seconds.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted and spread evenly in crust.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes or until chocolate is firm. Then arrange banana slices over chocolate.
Pour milk in a large bowl and add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk for 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon over bananas and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 4 hours until ready to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well and shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown in oleo over medium heat and drain.
Place in baking dish.
Combine cornstarch, vinegar and sugar in saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until clear and thick. Stir in remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: vicki's pizza
directions: Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
With pastry blender, cut in Crisco. Dissolve yeast in water. Add to flour mixture. Beat vigorously 2 minutes. Dust surface.
Knead 25 times.
Let rest 10 to 15 minutes. Spread on greased pan.
Top with warm sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Yields 1 cookie sheet size pizza.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer until thick.
Serve on hamburger buns with pickles and onions.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into dishes or large bowl.
Chill 30 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: super bowl chicken
directions: Mix the Ricotta, Mozzarella and spinach together.
Make a pocket between the skin and the chicken breast or thigh.
Fill the pocket with the cheese and spinach mixture.
Place the chicken in a large baking pan.
Brush with olive oil.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, basil and Romano cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes longer. Serves 6 to 8.

title: crunchy beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni, using package directions; drain.
Brown ground beef in large skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Add macaroni, mushroom soup, tomatoes, cheese, green pepper and seasoned salt; mix well.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix all liquid ingredients.
Layer in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish, starting with chicken, chips and liquid mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham 'n cheese strata
directions: Cover bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish with half of bread cubes.
Layer broccoli, ham and cheese over bread.
Top with remaining bread cubes.
Combine eggs, milk, onion, salt and mustard; pour over strata.
Refrigerate, covered, several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven until tests done when knife inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream together butter or margarine, brown sugar and vanilla. Add flour and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and chopped nuts and mix well.
Press mixture into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
While still warm, cut into squares.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain and mash.
Add butter, onions, cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Put in dish; top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crackers are brown.

title: virginia's 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: fruited champagne punch(24 servings, 4 ounces each)
directions: Day before serving:
In pitcher, combine 2 cups orange juice with the water.
Pour 2 cups orange juice mixture into a 3 cup ring mold.
Reserve remaining orange juice mixture.
Freeze mold until firm (about 3 hours).
Arrange grapes, orange slices and strawberries around top of mold.
Fill with reserved orange juice mixture.
Freeze.

title: buttermilk drop cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop cookies by teaspoon and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon candy popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a large bowl and set aside.
In a saucepan, combine butter, corn syrup and candies;
bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour over popcorn and mix thoroughly.
Turn into two greased 15 inch x l0 inch. x 1 inch baking pans.
Bake at 250 degrees for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and place on waxed paper to cool.
Break apart;
store in airtight containers or plastic bags.
Yield: 8 quarts.

title: ham and cheddar ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, Worcestershire, garlic powder and Ranch dressing packet together and blend. Add shredded cheese a little at a time (fold in). Add ham a little at a time (fold in). Mold into a ball, using a piece of plastic wrap sprayed with cooking spray to mold it (this keeps the ball from sticking to the plastic). Roll in chopped pecans (chopped fine) and chill wrapped up in plastic. Serve with crackers and fruit.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the raisins and water.
Cool.
Add soda to warm raisins.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and blend together real well.
Add dry ingredients and add soda and warm raisins.
Mix together until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken sesame
directions: Mix cooking oil, soy sauce, garlic and Accent.
Marinate chicken pieces 2 hours in oil mixture, turning occasionally.
Bake or broil chicken until done.
Sprinkle sesame seed on chicken the last 10 minutes.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix limeade, Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and food coloring together.
Pour in crust and freeze.

title: pork loin hash casserole
directions: Brown pork tenderloin in skillet.
In bowl, combine soup, milk, sour cream, half of shredded cheese and half of the French fried onions and mix into hash browns.
Place potato mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place pork loin on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and French onions on top.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Eat and enjoy.

title: carrot salad
directions: Place carrots and some water in blender; chop and drain in colander.
Add raisins and mix.
Let stand 30 minutes.
I mix from time to time.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar and sour cream; stir into carrots and raisins.
Serve on salad plate lined with lettuce leaf.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Do not add walnuts to salad until ready to serve as they will become soggy and spoil the salad!
Wait until the last minute.
Stores well in refrigerator. Tastes great!

title: apple bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and soda and add.
Add chopped apples and walnuts.
Batter will be very thick.
Place in a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan while still warm.
Cover with sugar and wrap in foil.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 9-inch pie plate.
With hand, mash and spread dough to sides and in bottom to desired thickness.
